2845
2846int RGWListBucket::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
2847{
2848 op_ret = get_params(y);
2849 if (op_ret < 0) {
2850 return op_ret;
2851 }
2852 if (!prefix.empty())
2853 s->env.emplace("s3:prefix", prefix);
2854
2855 if (!delimiter.empty())
2856 s->env.emplace("s3:delimiter", delimiter);
2857
2858 s->env.emplace("s3:max-keys", std::to_string(max));
2859
2860 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s, false);
2861 if (has_s3_resource_tag)
2862 rgw_iam_add_buckettags(this, s);
2863
2864 if (!verify_bucket_permission(this,
2865 s,
2866 list_versions ?
2867 rgw::IAM::s3ListBucketVersions :
2868 rgw::IAM::s3ListBucket)) {
2869 return -EACCES;
2870 }
2871
2872 return 0;
2873}
2874
2875int RGWListBucket::parse_max_keys()
2876{
2877 // Bound max value of max-keys to configured value for security
2878 // Bound min value of max-keys to '0'
2879 // Some S3 clients explicitly send max-keys=0 to detect if the bucket is
2880 // empty without listing any items.
2881 return parse_value_and_bound(max_keys, max, 0,
2882 g_conf().get_val<uint64_t>("rgw_max_listing_results"),
2883 default_max);
2884}
2885
2886void RGWListBucket::pre_exec()
2887{
2888 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
2889}
2890
2891void RGWListBucket::execute(optional_yield y)
2892{
2893 if (!s->bucket_exists) {
2894 op_ret = -ERR_NO_SUCH_BUCKET;
2895 return;
2896 }
2897
2898 if (allow_unordered && !delimiter.empty()) {
2899 ldpp_dout(this, 0) <<
2900 "ERROR: unordered bucket listing requested with a delimiter" << dendl;
2901 op_ret = -EINVAL;
2902 return;
2903 }
2904
2905 if (need_container_stats()) {
2906 op_ret = s->bucket->update_container_stats(s);
2907 }
2908
2909 rgw::sal::Bucket::ListParams params;
2910 params.prefix = prefix;
2911 params.delim = delimiter;
2912 params.marker = marker;
2913 params.end_marker = end_marker;
2914 params.list_versions = list_versions;
2915 params.allow_unordered = allow_unordered;
2916 params.shard_id = shard_id;
2917
2918 rgw::sal::Bucket::ListResults results;
2919
2920 op_ret = s->bucket->list(this, params, max, results, y);
2921 if (op_ret >= 0) {
2922 next_marker = results.next_marker;
2923 is_truncated = results.is_truncated;
2924 objs = std::move(results.objs);
2925 common_prefixes = std::move(results.common_prefixes);
2926 }
2927}

2946
2947int RGWCreateBucket::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
2948{
2949 /* This check is mostly needed for S3 that doesn't support account ACL.
2950 * Swift doesn't allow to delegate any permission to an anonymous user,
2951 * so it will become an early exit in such case. */
2952 if (s->auth.identity->is_anonymous()) {
2953 return -EACCES;
2954 }
2955
2956 rgw_bucket bucket;
2957 bucket.name = s->bucket_name;
2958 bucket.tenant = s->bucket_tenant;
2959 ARN arn = ARN(bucket);
2960 if (!verify_user_permission(this, s, arn, rgw::IAM::s3CreateBucket)) {
2961 return -EACCES;
2962 }
2963
2964 if (s->user->get_tenant() != s->bucket_tenant) {
2965 //AssumeRole is meant for cross account access
2966 if (s->auth.identity->get_identity_type() != TYPE_ROLE) {
2967 ldpp_dout(this, 10) << "user cannot create a bucket in a different tenant"
2968 << " (user_id.tenant=" << s->user->get_tenant()
2969 << " requested=" << s->bucket_tenant << ")"
2970 << dendl;
2971 return -EACCES;
2972 }
2973 }
2974
2975 if (s->user->get_max_buckets() < 0) {
2976 return -EPERM;
2977 }
2978
2979 if (s->user->get_max_buckets()) {
2980 rgw::sal::BucketList buckets;
2981 string marker;
2982 op_ret = s->user->list_buckets(this, marker, string(), s->user->get_max_buckets(),
2983 false, buckets, y);
2984 if (op_ret < 0) {
2985 return op_ret;
2986 }
2987
2988 if ((int)buckets.count() >= s->user->get_max_buckets()) {
2989 return -ERR_TOO_MANY_BUCKETS;
2990 }
2991 }
2992
2993 return 0;
2994}
2995
2996void RGWCreateBucket::pre_exec()
2997{
2998 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
2999}
3000
3001static void prepare_add_del_attrs(const map<string, bufferlist>& orig_attrs,
3002 map<string, bufferlist>& out_attrs,
3003 map<string, bufferlist>& out_rmattrs)
3004{
3005 for (const auto& kv : orig_attrs) {
3006 const string& name = kv.first;
3007
3008 /* Check if the attr is user-defined metadata item. */
3009 if (name.compare(0, sizeof(RGW_ATTR_META_PREFIX) - 1,
3010 RGW_ATTR_META_PREFIX) == 0) {
3011 /* For the objects all existing meta attrs have to be removed. */
3012 out_rmattrs[name] = kv.second;
3013 } else if (out_attrs.find(name) == std::end(out_attrs)) {
3014 out_attrs[name] = kv.second;
3015 }
3016 }
3017}
3018
3019/* Fuse resource metadata basing on original attributes in @orig_attrs, set
3020 * of _custom_ attribute names to remove in @rmattr_names and attributes in
3021 * @out_attrs. Place results in @out_attrs.
3022 *
3023 * NOTE: it's supposed that all special attrs already present in @out_attrs
3024 * will be preserved without any change. Special attributes are those which
3025 * names start with RGW_ATTR_META_PREFIX. They're complement to custom ones
3026 * used for X-Account-Meta-*, X-Container-Meta-*, X-Amz-Meta and so on. */
3027static void prepare_add_del_attrs(const map<string, bufferlist>& orig_attrs,
3028 const set<string>& rmattr_names,
3029 map<string, bufferlist>& out_attrs)
3030{
3031 for (const auto& kv : orig_attrs) {
3032 const string& name = kv.first;
3033
3034 /* Check if the attr is user-defined metadata item. */
3035 if (name.compare(0, strlen(RGW_ATTR_META_PREFIX),
3036 RGW_ATTR_META_PREFIX) == 0) {
3037 /* For the buckets all existing meta attrs are preserved,
3038 except those that are listed in rmattr_names. */
3039 if (rmattr_names.find(name) != std::end(rmattr_names)) {
3040 const auto aiter = out_attrs.find(name);
3041
3042 if (aiter != std::end(out_attrs)) {
3043 out_attrs.erase(aiter);
3044 }
3045 } else {
3046 /* emplace() won't alter the map if the key is already present.
3047 * This behaviour is fully intensional here. */
3048 out_attrs.emplace(kv);
3049 }
3050 } else if (out_attrs.find(name) == std::end(out_attrs)) {
3051 out_attrs[name] = kv.second;
3052 }
3053 }
3054}
3055
3056
3057static void populate_with_generic_attrs(const req_state * const s,
3058 map<string, bufferlist>& out_attrs)
3059{
3060 for (const auto& kv : s->generic_attrs) {
3061 bufferlist& attrbl = out_attrs[kv.first];
3062 const string& val = kv.second;
3063 attrbl.clear();
3064 attrbl.append(val.c_str(), val.size() + 1);
3065 }
3066}
3067
3068
3069static int filter_out_quota_info(std::map<std::string, bufferlist>& add_attrs,
3070 const std::set<std::string>& rmattr_names,
3071 RGWQuotaInfo& quota,
3072 bool * quota_extracted = nullptr)
3073{
3074 bool extracted = false;
3075
3076 /* Put new limit on max objects. */
3077 auto iter = add_attrs.find(RGW_ATTR_QUOTA_NOBJS);
3078 std::string err;
3079 if (std::end(add_attrs) != iter) {
3080 quota.max_objects =
3081 static_cast<int64_t>(strict_strtoll(iter->second.c_str(), 10, &err));
3082 if (!err.empty()) {
3083 return -EINVAL;
3084 }
3085 add_attrs.erase(iter);
3086 extracted = true;
3087 }
3088
3089 /* Put new limit on bucket (container) size. */
3090 iter = add_attrs.find(RGW_ATTR_QUOTA_MSIZE);
3091 if (iter != add_attrs.end()) {
3092 quota.max_size =
3093 static_cast<int64_t>(strict_strtoll(iter->second.c_str(), 10, &err));
3094 if (!err.empty()) {
3095 return -EINVAL;
3096 }
3097 add_attrs.erase(iter);
3098 extracted = true;
3099 }
3100
3101 for (const auto& name : rmattr_names) {
3102 /* Remove limit on max objects. */
3103 if (name.compare(RGW_ATTR_QUOTA_NOBJS) == 0) {
3104 quota.max_objects = -1;
3105 extracted = true;
3106 }
3107
3108 /* Remove limit on max bucket size. */
3109 if (name.compare(RGW_ATTR_QUOTA_MSIZE) == 0) {
3110 quota.max_size = -1;
3111 extracted = true;
3112 }
3113 }
3114
3115 /* Swift requries checking on raw usage instead of the 4 KiB rounded one. */
3116 quota.check_on_raw = true;
3117 quota.enabled = quota.max_size > 0 || quota.max_objects > 0;
3118
3119 if (quota_extracted) {
3120 *quota_extracted = extracted;
3121 }
3122
3123 return 0;
3124}
3125
3126
3127static void filter_out_website(std::map<std::string, ceph::bufferlist>& add_attrs,
3128 const std::set<std::string>& rmattr_names,
3129 RGWBucketWebsiteConf& ws_conf)
3130{
3131 std::string lstval;
3132
3133 /* Let's define a mapping between each custom attribute and the memory where
3134 * attribute's value should be stored. The memory location is expressed by
3135 * a non-const reference. */
3136 const auto mapping = {
3137 std::make_pair(RGW_ATTR_WEB_INDEX, std::ref(ws_conf.index_doc_suffix)),
3138 std::make_pair(RGW_ATTR_WEB_ERROR, std::ref(ws_conf.error_doc)),
3139 std::make_pair(RGW_ATTR_WEB_LISTINGS, std::ref(lstval)),
3140 std::make_pair(RGW_ATTR_WEB_LIST_CSS, std::ref(ws_conf.listing_css_doc)),
3141 std::make_pair(RGW_ATTR_SUBDIR_MARKER, std::ref(ws_conf.subdir_marker))
3142 };
3143
3144 for (const auto& kv : mapping) {
3145 const char * const key = kv.first;
3146 auto& target = kv.second;
3147
3148 auto iter = add_attrs.find(key);
3149
3150 if (std::end(add_attrs) != iter) {
3151 /* The "target" is a reference to ws_conf. */
3152 target = iter->second.c_str();
3153 add_attrs.erase(iter);
3154 }
3155
3156 if (rmattr_names.count(key)) {
3157 target = std::string();
3158 }
3159 }
3160
3161 if (! lstval.empty()) {
3162 ws_conf.listing_enabled = boost::algorithm::iequals(lstval, "true");
3163 }
3164}
3165
3166
3167void RGWCreateBucket::execute(optional_yield y)
3168{
3169 buffer::list aclbl;
3170 buffer::list corsbl;
3171 string bucket_name = rgw_make_bucket_entry_name(s->bucket_tenant, s->bucket_name);
3172 rgw_raw_obj obj(store->get_zone()->get_params().domain_root, bucket_name);
3173
3174 op_ret = get_params(y);
3175 if (op_ret < 0)
3176 return;
3177
3178 if (!relaxed_region_enforcement &&
3179 !location_constraint.empty() &&
3180 !store->get_zone()->has_zonegroup_api(location_constraint)) {
3181 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "location constraint (" << location_constraint << ")"
3182 << " can't be found." << dendl;
3183 op_ret = -ERR_INVALID_LOCATION_CONSTRAINT;
3184 s->err.message = "The specified location-constraint is not valid";
3185 return;
3186 }
3187
3188 if (!relaxed_region_enforcement && !store->get_zone()->get_zonegroup().is_master_zonegroup() && !location_constraint.empty() &&
3189 store->get_zone()->get_zonegroup().api_name != location_constraint) {
3190 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "location constraint (" << location_constraint << ")"
3191 << " doesn't match zonegroup" << " (" << store->get_zone()->get_zonegroup().api_name << ")"
3192 << dendl;
3193 op_ret = -ERR_INVALID_LOCATION_CONSTRAINT;
3194 s->err.message = "The specified location-constraint is not valid";
3195 return;
3196 }
3197
3198 const auto& zonegroup = store->get_zone()->get_zonegroup();
3199 if (!placement_rule.name.empty() &&
3200 !zonegroup.placement_targets.count(placement_rule.name)) {
3201 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "placement target (" << placement_rule.name << ")"
3202 << " doesn't exist in the placement targets of zonegroup"
3203 << " (" << store->get_zone()->get_zonegroup().api_name << ")" << dendl;
3204 op_ret = -ERR_INVALID_LOCATION_CONSTRAINT;
3205 s->err.message = "The specified placement target does not exist";
3206 return;
3207 }
3208
3209 /* we need to make sure we read bucket info, it's not read before for this
3210 * specific request */
3211 {
3212 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Bucket> tmp_bucket;
3213 op_ret = store->get_bucket(this, s->user.get(), s->bucket_tenant,
3214 s->bucket_name, &tmp_bucket, y);
3215 if (op_ret < 0 && op_ret != -ENOENT)
3216 return;
3217 s->bucket_exists = (op_ret != -ENOENT);
3218
3219 if (s->bucket_exists) {
3220 if (!s->system_request &&
3221 store->get_zone()->get_zonegroup().get_id() !=
3222 tmp_bucket->get_info().zonegroup) {
3223 op_ret = -EEXIST;
3224 return;
3225 }
3226 /* Initialize info from req_state */
3227 info = tmp_bucket->get_info();
3228 }
3229 }
3230
3231 s->bucket_owner.set_id(s->user->get_id()); /* XXX dang use s->bucket->owner */
3232 s->bucket_owner.set_name(s->user->get_display_name());
3233
3234 string zonegroup_id;
3235
3236 if (s->system_request) {
3237 zonegroup_id = s->info.args.get(RGW_SYS_PARAM_PREFIX "zonegroup");
3238 if (zonegroup_id.empty()) {
3239 zonegroup_id = store->get_zone()->get_zonegroup().get_id();
3240 }
3241 } else {
3242 zonegroup_id = store->get_zone()->get_zonegroup().get_id();
3243 }
3244
3245 /* Encode special metadata first as we're using std::map::emplace under
3246 * the hood. This method will add the new items only if the map doesn't
3247 * contain such keys yet. */
3248 policy.encode(aclbl);
3249 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_ACL, std::move(aclbl));
3250
3251 if (has_cors) {
3252 cors_config.encode(corsbl);
3253 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_CORS, std::move(corsbl));
3254 }
3255
3256 RGWQuotaInfo quota_info;
3257 const RGWQuotaInfo * pquota_info = nullptr;
3258 if (need_metadata_upload()) {
3259 /* It's supposed that following functions WILL NOT change any special
3260 * attributes (like RGW_ATTR_ACL) if they are already present in attrs. */
3261 op_ret = rgw_get_request_metadata(this, s->cct, s->info, attrs, false);
3262 if (op_ret < 0) {
3263 return;
3264 }
3265 prepare_add_del_attrs(s->bucket_attrs, rmattr_names, attrs);
3266 populate_with_generic_attrs(s, attrs);
3267
3268 op_ret = filter_out_quota_info(attrs, rmattr_names, quota_info);
3269 if (op_ret < 0) {
3270 return;
3271 } else {
3272 pquota_info = &quota_info;
3273 }
3274
3275 /* Web site of Swift API. */
3276 filter_out_website(attrs, rmattr_names, info.website_conf);
3277 info.has_website = !info.website_conf.is_empty();
3278 }
3279
3280 rgw_bucket tmp_bucket;
3281 tmp_bucket.tenant = s->bucket_tenant; /* ignored if bucket exists */
3282 tmp_bucket.name = s->bucket_name;
3283
3284 /* Handle updates of the metadata for Swift's object versioning. */
3285 if (swift_ver_location) {
3286 info.swift_ver_location = *swift_ver_location;
3287 info.swift_versioning = (! swift_ver_location->empty());
3288 }
3289
3290 /* We're replacing bucket with the newly created one */
3291 ldpp_dout(this, 10) << "user=" << s->user << " bucket=" << tmp_bucket << dendl;
3292 op_ret = s->user->create_bucket(this, tmp_bucket, zonegroup_id,
3293 placement_rule,
3294 info.swift_ver_location,
3295 pquota_info, policy, attrs, info, ep_objv,
3296 true, obj_lock_enabled, &s->bucket_exists, s->info,
3297 &s->bucket, y);
3298
3299 /* continue if EEXIST and create_bucket will fail below. this way we can
3300 * recover from a partial create by retrying it. */
3301 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "rgw_create_bucket returned ret=" << op_ret << " bucket=" << s->bucket.get() << dendl;
3302
3303 if (op_ret)
3304 return;
3305
3306 const bool existed = s->bucket_exists;
3307 if (need_metadata_upload() && existed) {
3308 /* OK, it looks we lost race with another request. As it's required to
3309 * handle metadata fusion and upload, the whole operation becomes very
3310 * similar in nature to PutMetadataBucket. However, as the attrs may
3311 * changed in the meantime, we have to refresh. */
3312 short tries = 0;
3313 do {
3314 map<string, bufferlist> battrs;
3315
3316 op_ret = s->bucket->load_bucket(this, y);
3317 if (op_ret < 0) {
3318 return;
3319 } else if (!s->bucket->is_owner(s->user.get())) {
3320 /* New bucket doesn't belong to the account we're operating on. */
3321 op_ret = -EEXIST;
3322 return;
3323 } else {
3324 s->bucket_attrs = s->bucket->get_attrs();
3325 }
3326
3327 attrs.clear();
3328
3329 op_ret = rgw_get_request_metadata(this, s->cct, s->info, attrs, false);
3330 if (op_ret < 0) {
3331 return;
3332 }
3333 prepare_add_del_attrs(s->bucket_attrs, rmattr_names, attrs);
3334 populate_with_generic_attrs(s, attrs);
3335 op_ret = filter_out_quota_info(attrs, rmattr_names, s->bucket->get_info().quota);
3336 if (op_ret < 0) {
3337 return;
3338 }
3339
3340 /* Handle updates of the metadata for Swift's object versioning. */
3341 if (swift_ver_location) {
3342 s->bucket->get_info().swift_ver_location = *swift_ver_location;
3343 s->bucket->get_info().swift_versioning = (! swift_ver_location->empty());
3344 }
3345
3346 /* Web site of Swift API. */
3347 filter_out_website(attrs, rmattr_names, s->bucket->get_info().website_conf);
3348 s->bucket->get_info().has_website = !s->bucket->get_info().website_conf.is_empty();
3349
3350 /* This will also set the quota on the bucket. */
3351 op_ret = s->bucket->merge_and_store_attrs(this, attrs, y);
3352 } while (op_ret == -ECANCELED && tries++ < 20);
3353
3354 /* Restore the proper return code. */
3355 if (op_ret >= 0) {
3356 op_ret = -ERR_BUCKET_EXISTS;
3357 }
3358 }
3359}
3360
3361int RGWDeleteBucket::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
3362{
3363 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s, false);
3364 if (has_s3_resource_tag)
3365 rgw_iam_add_buckettags(this, s);
3366
3367 if (!verify_bucket_permission(this, s, rgw::IAM::s3DeleteBucket)) {
3368 return -EACCES;
3369 }
3370
3371 return 0;
3372}
3373
3374void RGWDeleteBucket::pre_exec()
3375{
3376 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
3377}
3378
3379void RGWDeleteBucket::execute(optional_yield y)
3380{
3381 if (s->bucket_name.empty()) {
3382 op_ret = -EINVAL;
3383 return;
3384 }
3385
3386 if (!s->bucket_exists) {
3387 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: bucket " << s->bucket_name << " not found" << dendl;
3388 op_ret = -ERR_NO_SUCH_BUCKET;
3389 return;
3390 }
3391 RGWObjVersionTracker ot;
3392 ot.read_version = s->bucket->get_version();
3393
3394 if (s->system_request) {
3395 string tag = s->info.args.get(RGW_SYS_PARAM_PREFIX "tag");
3396 string ver_str = s->info.args.get(RGW_SYS_PARAM_PREFIX "ver");
3397 if (!tag.empty()) {
3398 ot.read_version.tag = tag;
3399 uint64_t ver;
3400 string err;
3401 ver = strict_strtol(ver_str.c_str(), 10, &err);
3402 if (!err.empty()) {
3403 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "failed to parse ver param" << dendl;
3404 op_ret = -EINVAL;
3405 return;
3406 }
3407 ot.read_version.ver = ver;
3408 }
3409 }
3410
3411 op_ret = s->bucket->sync_user_stats(this, y);
3412 if ( op_ret < 0) {
3413 ldpp_dout(this, 1) << "WARNING: failed to sync user stats before bucket delete: op_ret= " << op_ret << dendl;
3414 }
3415
3416 op_ret = s->bucket->check_empty(this, y);
3417 if (op_ret < 0) {
3418 return;
3419 }
3420
3421 bufferlist in_data;
3422 op_ret = store->forward_request_to_master(this, s->user.get(), &ot.read_version, in_data, nullptr, s->info, y);
3423 if (op_ret < 0) {
3424 if (op_ret == -ENOENT) {
3425 /* adjust error, we want to return with NoSuchBucket and not
3426 * NoSuchKey */
3427 op_ret = -ERR_NO_SUCH_BUCKET;
3428 }
3429 return;
3430 }
3431
3432 op_ret = rgw_remove_sse_s3_bucket_key(s);
3433 if (op_ret != 0) {
3434 // do nothing; it will already have been logged
3435 }
3436
3437 op_ret = s->bucket->remove_bucket(this, false, false, nullptr, y);
3438 if (op_ret < 0 && op_ret == -ECANCELED) {
3439 // lost a race, either with mdlog sync or another delete bucket operation.
3440 // in either case, we've already called ctl.bucket->unlink_bucket()
3441 op_ret = 0;
3442 }
3443
3444 return;
3445}
3446
3447int RGWPutObj::init_processing(optional_yield y) {
3448 copy_source = url_decode(s->info.env->get("HTTP_X_AMZ_COPY_SOURCE", ""));
3449 copy_source_range = s->info.env->get("HTTP_X_AMZ_COPY_SOURCE_RANGE");
3450 size_t pos;
3451 int ret;
3452
3453 /* handle x-amz-copy-source */
3454 std::string_view cs_view(copy_source);
3455 if (! cs_view.empty()) {
3456 if (cs_view[0] == '/')
3457 cs_view.remove_prefix(1);
3458 copy_source_bucket_name = std::string(cs_view);
3459 pos = copy_source_bucket_name.find("/");
3460 if (pos == std::string::npos) {
3461 ret = -EINVAL;
3462 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << "x-amz-copy-source bad format" << dendl;
3463 return ret;
3464 }
3465 copy_source_object_name =
3466 copy_source_bucket_name.substr(pos + 1, copy_source_bucket_name.size());
3467 copy_source_bucket_name = copy_source_bucket_name.substr(0, pos);
3468#define VERSION_ID_STR "?versionId="
3469 pos = copy_source_object_name.find(VERSION_ID_STR);
3470 if (pos == std::string::npos) {
3471 copy_source_object_name = url_decode(copy_source_object_name);
3472 } else {
3473 copy_source_version_id =
3474 copy_source_object_name.substr(pos + sizeof(VERSION_ID_STR) - 1);
3475 copy_source_object_name =
3476 url_decode(copy_source_object_name.substr(0, pos));
3477 }
3478 pos = copy_source_bucket_name.find(":");
3479 if (pos == std::string::npos) {
3480 // if tenant is not specified in x-amz-copy-source, use tenant of the requester
3481 copy_source_tenant_name = s->user->get_tenant();
3482 } else {
3483 copy_source_tenant_name = copy_source_bucket_name.substr(0, pos);
3484 copy_source_bucket_name = copy_source_bucket_name.substr(pos + 1, copy_source_bucket_name.size());
3485 if (copy_source_bucket_name.empty()) {
3486 ret = -EINVAL;
3487 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << "source bucket name is empty" << dendl;
3488 return ret;
3489 }
3490 }
3491 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Bucket> bucket;
3492 ret = store->get_bucket(this, s->user.get(), copy_source_tenant_name, copy_source_bucket_name,
3493 &bucket, y);
3494 if (ret < 0) {
3495 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << __func__ << "(): get_bucket() returned ret=" << ret << dendl;
3496 if (ret == -ENOENT) {
3497 ret = -ERR_NO_SUCH_BUCKET;
3498 }
3499 return ret;
3500 }
3501
3502 ret = bucket->load_bucket(this, y);
3503 if (ret < 0) {
3504 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << __func__ << "(): load_bucket() returned ret=" << ret << dendl;
3505 return ret;
3506 }
3507 copy_source_bucket_info = bucket->get_info();
3508
3509 /* handle x-amz-copy-source-range */
3510 if (copy_source_range) {
3511 string range = copy_source_range;
3512 pos = range.find("bytes=");
3513 if (pos == std::string::npos || pos != 0) {
3514 ret = -EINVAL;
3515 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << "x-amz-copy-source-range bad format" << dendl;
3516 return ret;
3517 }
3518 /* 6 is the length of "bytes=" */
3519 range = range.substr(pos + 6);
3520 pos = range.find("-");
3521 if (pos == std::string::npos) {
3522 ret = -EINVAL;
3523 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << "x-amz-copy-source-range bad format" << dendl;
3524 return ret;
3525 }
3526 string first = range.substr(0, pos);
3527 string last = range.substr(pos + 1);
3528 if (first.find_first_not_of("0123456789") != std::string::npos ||
3529 last.find_first_not_of("0123456789") != std::string::npos) {
3530 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << "x-amz-copy-source-range bad format not an integer" << dendl;
3531 ret = -EINVAL;
3532 return ret;
3533 }
3534 copy_source_range_fst = strtoull(first.c_str(), NULL, 10);
3535 copy_source_range_lst = strtoull(last.c_str(), NULL, 10);
3536 if (copy_source_range_fst > copy_source_range_lst) {
3537 ret = -ERANGE;
3538 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << "x-amz-copy-source-range bad format first number bigger than second" << dendl;
3539 return ret;
3540 }
3541 }
3542
3543 } /* copy_source */
3544 return RGWOp::init_processing(y);
3545}
3546
3547int RGWPutObj::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
3548{
3549 if (! copy_source.empty()) {
3550
3551 RGWAccessControlPolicy cs_acl(s->cct);
3552 boost::optional<Policy> policy;
3553 map<string, bufferlist> cs_attrs;
3554 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Bucket> cs_bucket;
3555 int ret = store->get_bucket(NULL, copy_source_bucket_info, &cs_bucket);
3556 if (ret < 0)
3557 return ret;
3558
3559 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Object> cs_object =
3560 cs_bucket->get_object(rgw_obj_key(copy_source_object_name, copy_source_version_id));
3561
3562 cs_object->set_atomic(s->obj_ctx);
3563 cs_object->set_prefetch_data(s->obj_ctx);
3564
3565 /* check source object permissions */
3566 if (ret = read_obj_policy(this, store, s, copy_source_bucket_info, cs_attrs, &cs_acl, nullptr,
3567 policy, cs_bucket.get(), cs_object.get(), y, true); ret < 0) {
3568 return ret;
3569 }
3570
3571 /* admin request overrides permission checks */
3572 if (! s->auth.identity->is_admin_of(cs_acl.get_owner().get_id())) {
3573 if (policy || ! s->iam_user_policies.empty() || !s->session_policies.empty()) {
3574 //add source object tags for permission evaluation
3575 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, policy, s->iam_user_policies, s->session_policies);
3576 if (has_s3_existing_tag || has_s3_resource_tag)
3577 rgw_iam_add_objtags(this, s, cs_object.get(), has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag);
3578 auto usr_policy_res = Effect::Pass;
3579 rgw::ARN obj_arn(cs_object->get_obj());
3580 for (auto& user_policy : s->iam_user_policies) {
3581 if (usr_policy_res = user_policy.eval(s->env, *s->auth.identity,
3582 cs_object->get_instance().empty() ?
3583 rgw::IAM::s3GetObject :
3584 rgw::IAM::s3GetObjectVersion,
3585 obj_arn); usr_policy_res == Effect::Deny)
3586 return -EACCES;
3587 else if (usr_policy_res == Effect::Allow)
3588 break;
3589 }
3590 rgw::IAM::Effect e = Effect::Pass;
3591 if (policy) {
3592 rgw::ARN obj_arn(cs_object->get_obj());
3593 e = policy->eval(s->env, *s->auth.identity,
3594 cs_object->get_instance().empty() ?
3595 rgw::IAM::s3GetObject :
3596 rgw::IAM::s3GetObjectVersion,
3597 obj_arn);
3598 }
3599 if (e == Effect::Deny) {
3600 return -EACCES;
3601 } else if (usr_policy_res == Effect::Pass && e == Effect::Pass &&
3602 !cs_acl.verify_permission(this, *s->auth.identity, s->perm_mask,
3603 RGW_PERM_READ)) {
3604 return -EACCES;
3605 }
3606 rgw_iam_remove_objtags(this, s, cs_object.get(), has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag);
3607 } else if (!cs_acl.verify_permission(this, *s->auth.identity, s->perm_mask,
3608 RGW_PERM_READ)) {
3609 return -EACCES;
3610 }
3611 }
3612 }
3613
3614 if (s->bucket_access_conf && s->bucket_access_conf->block_public_acls()) {
3615 if (s->canned_acl.compare("public-read") ||
3616 s->canned_acl.compare("public-read-write") ||
3617 s->canned_acl.compare("authenticated-read"))
3618 return -EACCES;
3619 }
3620
3621 auto op_ret = get_params(y);
3622 if (op_ret < 0) {
3623 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "get_params() returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
3624 return op_ret;
3625 }
3626
3627 if (s->iam_policy || ! s->iam_user_policies.empty() || !s->session_policies.empty()) {
3628 rgw_add_grant_to_iam_environment(s->env, s);
3629
3630 rgw_add_to_iam_environment(s->env, "s3:x-amz-acl", s->canned_acl);
3631
3632 if (obj_tags != nullptr && obj_tags->count() > 0){
3633 auto tags = obj_tags->get_tags();
3634 for (const auto& kv: tags){
3635 rgw_add_to_iam_environment(s->env, "s3:RequestObjectTag/"+kv.first, kv.second);
3636 }
3637 }
3638
3639 constexpr auto encrypt_attr = "x-amz-server-side-encryption";
3640 constexpr auto s3_encrypt_attr = "s3:x-amz-server-side-encryption";
3641 auto enc_header = s->info.crypt_attribute_map.find(encrypt_attr);
3642 if (enc_header != s->info.crypt_attribute_map.end()){
3643 rgw_add_to_iam_environment(s->env, s3_encrypt_attr, enc_header->second);
3644 }
3645
3646 constexpr auto kms_attr = "x-amz-server-side-encryption-aws-kms-key-id";
3647 constexpr auto s3_kms_attr = "s3:x-amz-server-side-encryption-aws-kms-key-id";
3648 auto kms_header = s->info.crypt_attribute_map.find(kms_attr);
3649 if (kms_header != s->info.crypt_attribute_map.end()){
3650 rgw_add_to_iam_environment(s->env, s3_kms_attr, kms_header->second);
3651 }
3652
3653 // Add bucket tags for authorization
3654 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s, false);
3655 if (has_s3_resource_tag)
3656 rgw_iam_add_buckettags(this, s);
3657
3658 auto identity_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->iam_user_policies, s->env,
3659 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
3660 s->object->get_obj());
3661 if (identity_policy_res == Effect::Deny)
3662 return -EACCES;
3663
3664 rgw::IAM::Effect e = Effect::Pass;
3665 rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal princ_type = rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other;
3666 if (s->iam_policy) {
3667 ARN obj_arn(s->object->get_obj());
3668 e = s->iam_policy->eval(s->env, *s->auth.identity,
3669 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
3670 obj_arn,
3671 princ_type);
3672 }
3673 if (e == Effect::Deny) {
3674 return -EACCES;
3675 }
3676
3677 if (!s->session_policies.empty()) {
3678 auto session_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->session_policies, s->env,
3679 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
3680 s->object->get_obj());
3681 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
3682 return -EACCES;
3683 }
3684 if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Role) {
3685 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus intersection of session policy and bucket policy
3686 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) ||
3687 (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && e == Effect::Allow))
3688 return 0;
3689 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Session) {
3690 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus bucket policy
3691 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) || e == Effect::Allow)
3692 return 0;
3693 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other) {// there was no match in the bucket policy
3694 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow)
3695 return 0;
3696 }
3697 return -EACCES;
3698 }
3699 if (e == Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) {
3700 return 0;
3701 }
3702 }
3703
3704 if (!verify_bucket_permission_no_policy(this, s, RGW_PERM_WRITE)) {
3705 return -EACCES;
3706 }
3707
3708 return 0;
3709}
3710
3711
3712void RGWPutObj::pre_exec()
3713{
3714 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
3715}
3716
3717class RGWPutObj_CB : public RGWGetObj_Filter
3718{
3719 RGWPutObj *op;
3720public:
3721 explicit RGWPutObj_CB(RGWPutObj *_op) : op(_op) {}
3722 ~RGWPutObj_CB() override {}
3723
3724 int handle_data(bufferlist& bl, off_t bl_ofs, off_t bl_len) override {
3725 return op->get_data_cb(bl, bl_ofs, bl_len);
3726 }
3727};
3728
3729int RGWPutObj::get_data_cb(bufferlist& bl, off_t bl_ofs, off_t bl_len)
3730{
3731 bufferlist bl_tmp;
3732 bl.begin(bl_ofs).copy(bl_len, bl_tmp);
3733
3734 bl_aux.append(bl_tmp);
3735
3736 return bl_len;
3737}
3738
3739int RGWPutObj::get_data(const off_t fst, const off_t lst, bufferlist& bl)
3740{
3741 RGWPutObj_CB cb(this);
3742 RGWGetObj_Filter* filter = &cb;
3743 boost::optional<RGWGetObj_Decompress> decompress;
3744 std::unique_ptr<RGWGetObj_Filter> decrypt;
3745 RGWCompressionInfo cs_info;
3746 map<string, bufferlist> attrs;
3747 int ret = 0;
3748
3749 uint64_t obj_size;
3750 int64_t new_ofs, new_end;
3751
3752 new_ofs = fst;
3753 new_end = lst;
3754
3755 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Bucket> bucket;
3756 ret = store->get_bucket(nullptr, copy_source_bucket_info, &bucket);
3757 if (ret < 0)
3758 return ret;
3759
3760 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Object> obj = bucket->get_object(rgw_obj_key(copy_source_object_name, copy_source_version_id));
3761 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Object::ReadOp> read_op(obj->get_read_op(s->obj_ctx));
3762
3763 ret = read_op->prepare(s->yield, this);
3764 if (ret < 0)
3765 return ret;
3766
3767 obj_size = obj->get_obj_size();
3768
3769 bool need_decompress;
3770 op_ret = rgw_compression_info_from_attrset(obj->get_attrs(), need_decompress, cs_info);
3771 if (op_ret < 0) {
3772 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: failed to decode compression info" << dendl;
3773 return -EIO;
3774 }
3775
3776 bool partial_content = true;
3777 if (need_decompress)
3778 {
3779 obj_size = cs_info.orig_size;
3780 decompress.emplace(s->cct, &cs_info, partial_content, filter);
3781 filter = &*decompress;
3782 }
3783
3784 auto attr_iter = obj->get_attrs().find(RGW_ATTR_MANIFEST);
3785 op_ret = this->get_decrypt_filter(&decrypt,
3786 filter,
3787 obj->get_attrs(),
3788 attr_iter != obj->get_attrs().end() ? &(attr_iter->second) : nullptr);
3789 if (decrypt != nullptr) {
3790 filter = decrypt.get();
3791 }
3792 if (op_ret < 0) {
3793 return op_ret;
3794 }
3795
3796 ret = obj->range_to_ofs(obj_size, new_ofs, new_end);
3797 if (ret < 0)
3798 return ret;
3799
3800 filter->fixup_range(new_ofs, new_end);
3801 ret = read_op->iterate(this, new_ofs, new_end, filter, s->yield);
3802
3803 if (ret >= 0)
3804 ret = filter->flush();
3805
3806 bl.claim_append(bl_aux);
3807
3808 return ret;
3809}
3810
3811// special handling for compression type = "random" with multipart uploads
3812static CompressorRef get_compressor_plugin(const req_state *s,
3813 const std::string& compression_type)
3814{
3815 if (compression_type != "random") {
3816 return Compressor::create(s->cct, compression_type);
3817 }
3818
3819 bool is_multipart{false};
3820 const auto& upload_id = s->info.args.get("uploadId", &is_multipart);
3821
3822 if (!is_multipart) {
3823 return Compressor::create(s->cct, compression_type);
3824 }
3825
3826 // use a hash of the multipart upload id so all parts use the same plugin
3827 const auto alg = std::hash<std::string>{}(upload_id) % Compressor::COMP_ALG_LAST;
3828 if (alg == Compressor::COMP_ALG_NONE) {
3829 return nullptr;
3830 }
3831 return Compressor::create(s->cct, alg);
3832}
3833
3834void RGWPutObj::execute(optional_yield y)
3835{
3836 char supplied_md5_bin[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE + 1];
3837 char supplied_md5[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE * 2 + 1];
3838 char calc_md5[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE * 2 + 1];
3839 unsigned char m[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE];
3840 MD5 hash;
3841 // Allow use of MD5 digest in FIPS mode for non-cryptographic purposes
3842 hash.SetFlags(EVP_MD_CTX_FLAG_NON_FIPS_ALLOW);
3843 bufferlist bl, aclbl, bs;
3844 int len;
3845
3846 off_t fst;
3847 off_t lst;
3848
3849 bool need_calc_md5 = (dlo_manifest == NULL) && (slo_info == NULL);
3850 perfcounter->inc(l_rgw_put);
3851 // report latency on return
3852 auto put_lat = make_scope_guard([&] {
3853 perfcounter->tinc(l_rgw_put_lat, s->time_elapsed());
3854 });
3855
3856 op_ret = -EINVAL;
3857 if (rgw::sal::Object::empty(s->object.get())) {
3858 return;
3859 }
3860
3861 if (!s->bucket_exists) {
3862 op_ret = -ERR_NO_SUCH_BUCKET;
3863 return;
3864 }
3865
3866 op_ret = get_system_versioning_params(s, &olh_epoch, &version_id);
3867 if (op_ret < 0) {
3868 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "get_system_versioning_params() returned ret="
3869 << op_ret << dendl;
3870 return;
3871 }
3872
3873 if (supplied_md5_b64) {
3874 need_calc_md5 = true;
3875
3876 ldpp_dout(this, 15) << "supplied_md5_b64=" << supplied_md5_b64 << dendl;
3877 op_ret = ceph_unarmor(supplied_md5_bin, &supplied_md5_bin[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE + 1],
3878 supplied_md5_b64, supplied_md5_b64 + strlen(supplied_md5_b64));
3879 ldpp_dout(this, 15) << "ceph_armor ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
3880 if (op_ret != CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE) {
3881 op_ret = -ERR_INVALID_DIGEST;
3882 return;
3883 }
3884
3885 buf_to_hex((const unsigned char *)supplied_md5_bin, CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE, supplied_md5);
3886 ldpp_dout(this, 15) << "supplied_md5=" << supplied_md5 << dendl;
3887 }
3888
3889 if (!chunked_upload) { /* with chunked upload we don't know how big is the upload.
3890 we also check sizes at the end anyway */
3891 op_ret = s->bucket->check_quota(this, user_quota, bucket_quota, s->content_length, y);
3892 if (op_ret < 0) {
3893 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "check_quota() returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
3894 return;
3895 }
3896 }
3897
3898 if (supplied_etag) {
3899 strncpy(supplied_md5, supplied_etag, sizeof(supplied_md5) - 1);
3900 supplied_md5[sizeof(supplied_md5) - 1] = '\0';
3901 }
3902
3903 const bool multipart = !multipart_upload_id.empty();
3904 auto& obj_ctx = *static_cast<RGWObjectCtx*>(s->obj_ctx);
3905
3906 /* Handle object versioning of Swift API. */
3907 if (! multipart) {
3908 op_ret = s->object->swift_versioning_copy(s->obj_ctx, this, s->yield);
3909 if (op_ret < 0) {
3910 return;
3911 }
3912 }
3913
3914 // make reservation for notification if needed
3915 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Notification> res
3916 = store->get_notification(
3917 s->object.get(), s->src_object.get(), s,
3918 rgw::notify::ObjectCreatedPut);
3919 if(!multipart) {
3920 op_ret = res->publish_reserve(this, obj_tags.get());
3921 if (op_ret < 0) {
3922 return;
3923 }
3924 }
3925
3926 // create the object processor
3927 auto aio = rgw::make_throttle(s->cct->_conf->rgw_put_obj_min_window_size,
3928 s->yield);
3929 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Writer> processor;
3930
3931 rgw_placement_rule *pdest_placement = &s->dest_placement;
3932
3933 if (multipart) {
3934 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::MultipartUpload> upload;
3935 upload = s->bucket->get_multipart_upload(s->object->get_name(),
3936 multipart_upload_id);
3937 op_ret = upload->get_info(this, s->yield, s->obj_ctx, &pdest_placement);
3938
3939 s->trace->SetAttribute(tracing::rgw::UPLOAD_ID, multipart_upload_id);
3940 multipart_trace = tracing::rgw::tracer.add_span(name(), upload->get_trace());
3941
3942 if (op_ret < 0) {
3943 if (op_ret != -ENOENT) {
3944 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: get_multipart_info returned " << op_ret << ": " << cpp_strerror(-op_ret) << dendl;
3945 } else {// -ENOENT: raced with upload complete/cancel, no need to spam log
3946 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "failed to get multipart info (returned " << op_ret << ": " << cpp_strerror(-op_ret) << "): probably raced with upload complete / cancel" << dendl;
3947 }
3948 return;
3949 }
3950 /* upload will go out of scope, so copy the dest placement for later use */
3951 s->dest_placement = *pdest_placement;
3952 pdest_placement = &s->dest_placement;
3953 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "dest_placement for part=" << *pdest_placement << dendl;
3954 processor = upload->get_writer(this, s->yield, s->object->clone(),
3955 s->user->get_id(), obj_ctx, pdest_placement,
3956 multipart_part_num, multipart_part_str);
3957 } else if(append) {
3958 if (s->bucket->versioned()) {
3959 op_ret = -ERR_INVALID_BUCKET_STATE;
3960 return;
3961 }
3962 processor = store->get_append_writer(this, s->yield, s->object->clone(),
3963 s->bucket_owner.get_id(), obj_ctx,
3964 pdest_placement, s->req_id, position,
3965 &cur_accounted_size);
3966 } else {
3967 if (s->bucket->versioning_enabled()) {
3968 if (!version_id.empty()) {
3969 s->object->set_instance(version_id);
3970 } else {
3971 s->object->gen_rand_obj_instance_name();
3972 version_id = s->object->get_instance();
3973 }
3974 }
3975 processor = store->get_atomic_writer(this, s->yield, s->object->clone(),
3976 s->bucket_owner.get_id(), obj_ctx,
3977 pdest_placement, olh_epoch, s->req_id);
3978 }
3979
3980 op_ret = processor->prepare(s->yield);
3981 if (op_ret < 0) {
3982 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "processor->prepare() returned ret=" << op_ret
3983 << dendl;
3984 return;
3985 }
3986 if ((! copy_source.empty()) && !copy_source_range) {
3987 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Bucket> bucket;
3988 op_ret = store->get_bucket(nullptr, copy_source_bucket_info, &bucket);
3989 if (op_ret < 0) {
3990 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: failed to get bucket with error" << op_ret << dendl;
3991 return;
3992 }
3993 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Object> obj =
3994 bucket->get_object(rgw_obj_key(copy_source_object_name, copy_source_version_id));
3995
3996 RGWObjState *astate;
3997 op_ret = obj->get_obj_state(this, &obj_ctx, &astate, s->yield);
3998 if (op_ret < 0) {
3999 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: get copy source obj state returned with error" << op_ret << dendl;
4000 return;
4001 }
4002 bufferlist bl;
4003 if (astate->get_attr(RGW_ATTR_MANIFEST, bl)) {
4004 RGWObjManifest m;
4005 decode(m, bl);
4006 if (m.get_tier_type() == "cloud-s3") {
4007 op_ret = -ERR_INVALID_OBJECT_STATE;
4008 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: Cannot copy cloud tiered object. Failing with "
4009 << op_ret << dendl;
4010 return;
4011 }
4012 }
4013
4014 if (!astate->exists){
4015 op_ret = -ENOENT;
4016 return;
4017 }
4018 lst = astate->accounted_size - 1;
4019 } else {
4020 lst = copy_source_range_lst;
4021 }
4022 fst = copy_source_range_fst;
4023
4024 // no filters by default
4025 rgw::sal::DataProcessor *filter = processor.get();
4026
4027 const auto& compression_type = store->get_zone()->get_params().get_compression_type(*pdest_placement);
4028 CompressorRef plugin;
4029 boost::optional<RGWPutObj_Compress> compressor;
4030
4031 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::DataProcessor> encrypt;
4032
4033 if (!append) { // compression and encryption only apply to full object uploads
4034 op_ret = get_encrypt_filter(&encrypt, filter);
4035 if (op_ret < 0) {
4036 return;
4037 }
4038 if (encrypt != nullptr) {
4039 filter = &*encrypt;
4040 } else if (compression_type != "none") {
4041 plugin = get_compressor_plugin(s, compression_type);
4042 if (!plugin) {
4043 ldpp_dout(this, 1) << "Cannot load plugin for compression type "
4044 << compression_type << dendl;
4045 } else {
4046 compressor.emplace(s->cct, plugin, filter);
4047 filter = &*compressor;
4048 // always send incompressible hint when rgw is itself doing compression
4049 s->object->set_compressed(s->obj_ctx);
4050 }
4051 }
4052 }
4053 tracepoint(rgw_op, before_data_transfer, s->req_id.c_str());
4054 do {
4055 bufferlist data;
4056 if (fst > lst)
4057 break;
4058 if (copy_source.empty()) {
4059 len = get_data(data);
4060 } else {
4061 off_t cur_lst = min<off_t>(fst + s->cct->_conf->rgw_max_chunk_size - 1, lst);
4062 op_ret = get_data(fst, cur_lst, data);
4063 if (op_ret < 0)
4064 return;
4065 len = data.length();
4066 s->content_length += len;
4067 fst += len;
4068 }
4069 if (len < 0) {
4070 op_ret = len;
4071 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "get_data() returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
4072 return;
4073 } else if (len == 0) {
4074 break;
4075 }
4076
4077 if (need_calc_md5) {
4078 hash.Update((const unsigned char *)data.c_str(), data.length());
4079 }
4080
4081 /* update torrrent */
4082 torrent.update(data);
4083
4084 op_ret = filter->process(std::move(data), ofs);
4085 if (op_ret < 0) {
4086 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "processor->process() returned ret="
4087 << op_ret << dendl;
4088 return;
4089 }
4090
4091 ofs += len;
4092 } while (len > 0);
4093 tracepoint(rgw_op, after_data_transfer, s->req_id.c_str(), ofs);
4094
4095 // flush any data in filters
4096 op_ret = filter->process({}, ofs);
4097 if (op_ret < 0) {
4098 return;
4099 }
4100
4101 if (!chunked_upload && ofs != s->content_length) {
4102 op_ret = -ERR_REQUEST_TIMEOUT;
4103 return;
4104 }
4105 s->obj_size = ofs;
4106 s->object->set_obj_size(ofs);
4107
4108 perfcounter->inc(l_rgw_put_b, s->obj_size);
4109
4110 op_ret = do_aws4_auth_completion();
4111 if (op_ret < 0) {
4112 return;
4113 }
4114
4115 op_ret = s->bucket->check_quota(this, user_quota, bucket_quota, s->obj_size, y);
4116 if (op_ret < 0) {
4117 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "second check_quota() returned op_ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
4118 return;
4119 }
4120
4121 hash.Final(m);
4122
4123 if (compressor && compressor->is_compressed()) {
4124 bufferlist tmp;
4125 RGWCompressionInfo cs_info;
4126 cs_info.compression_type = plugin->get_type_name();
4127 cs_info.orig_size = s->obj_size;
4128 cs_info.compressor_message = compressor->get_compressor_message();
4129 cs_info.blocks = move(compressor->get_compression_blocks());
4130 encode(cs_info, tmp);
4131 attrs[RGW_ATTR_COMPRESSION] = tmp;
4132 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "storing " << RGW_ATTR_COMPRESSION
4133 << " with type=" << cs_info.compression_type
4134 << ", orig_size=" << cs_info.orig_size
4135 << ", blocks=" << cs_info.blocks.size() << dendl;
4136 }
4137
4138 buf_to_hex(m, CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE, calc_md5);
4139
4140 etag = calc_md5;
4141
4142 if (supplied_md5_b64 && strcmp(calc_md5, supplied_md5)) {
4143 op_ret = -ERR_BAD_DIGEST;
4144 return;
4145 }
4146
4147 policy.encode(aclbl);
4148 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_ACL, std::move(aclbl));
4149
4150 if (dlo_manifest) {
4151 op_ret = encode_dlo_manifest_attr(dlo_manifest, attrs);
4152 if (op_ret < 0) {
4153 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "bad user manifest: " << dlo_manifest << dendl;
4154 return;
4155 }
4156 }
4157
4158 if (slo_info) {
4159 bufferlist manifest_bl;
4160 encode(*slo_info, manifest_bl);
4161 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_SLO_MANIFEST, std::move(manifest_bl));
4162 }
4163
4164 if (supplied_etag && etag.compare(supplied_etag) != 0) {
4165 op_ret = -ERR_UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY;
4166 return;
4167 }
4168 bl.append(etag.c_str(), etag.size());
4169 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_ETAG, std::move(bl));
4170
4171 populate_with_generic_attrs(s, attrs);
4172 op_ret = rgw_get_request_metadata(this, s->cct, s->info, attrs);
4173 if (op_ret < 0) {
4174 return;
4175 }
4176 encode_delete_at_attr(delete_at, attrs);
4177 encode_obj_tags_attr(obj_tags.get(), attrs);
4178 rgw_cond_decode_objtags(s, attrs);
4179
4180 /* Add a custom metadata to expose the information whether an object
4181 * is an SLO or not. Appending the attribute must be performed AFTER
4182 * processing any input from user in order to prohibit overwriting. */
4183 if (slo_info) {
4184 bufferlist slo_userindicator_bl;
4185 slo_userindicator_bl.append("True", 4);
4186 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_SLO_UINDICATOR, std::move(slo_userindicator_bl));
4187 }
4188 if (obj_legal_hold) {
4189 bufferlist obj_legal_hold_bl;
4190 obj_legal_hold->encode(obj_legal_hold_bl);
4191 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_OBJECT_LEGAL_HOLD, std::move(obj_legal_hold_bl));
4192 }
4193 if (obj_retention) {
4194 bufferlist obj_retention_bl;
4195 obj_retention->encode(obj_retention_bl);
4196 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_OBJECT_RETENTION, std::move(obj_retention_bl));
4197 }
4198
4199 tracepoint(rgw_op, processor_complete_enter, s->req_id.c_str());
4200 op_ret = processor->complete(s->obj_size, etag, &mtime, real_time(), attrs,
4201 (delete_at ? *delete_at : real_time()), if_match, if_nomatch,
4202 (user_data.empty() ? nullptr : &user_data), nullptr, nullptr,
4203 s->yield);
4204 tracepoint(rgw_op, processor_complete_exit, s->req_id.c_str());
4205
4206 /* produce torrent */
4207 if (s->cct->_conf->rgw_torrent_flag && (ofs == torrent.get_data_len()))
4208 {
4209 torrent.init(s, store);
4210 torrent.set_create_date(mtime);
4211 op_ret = torrent.complete(y);
4212 if (0 != op_ret)
4213 {
4214 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: torrent.handle_data() returned " << op_ret << dendl;
4215 return;
4216 }
4217 }
4218
4219 // send request to notification manager
4220 int ret = res->publish_commit(this, s->obj_size, mtime, etag, s->object->get_instance());
4221 if (ret < 0) {
4222 ldpp_dout(this, 1) << "ERROR: publishing notification failed, with error: " << ret << dendl;
4223 // too late to rollback operation, hence op_ret is not set here
4224 }
4225}
4226
4227int RGWPostObj::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
4228{
4229 return 0;
4230}
4231
4232void RGWPostObj::pre_exec()
4233{
4234 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
4235}
4236
4237void RGWPostObj::execute(optional_yield y)
4238{
4239 boost::optional<RGWPutObj_Compress> compressor;
4240 CompressorRef plugin;
4241 char supplied_md5[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE * 2 + 1];
4242
4243 /* Read in the data from the POST form. */
4244 op_ret = get_params(y);
4245 if (op_ret < 0) {
4246 return;
4247 }
4248
4249 op_ret = verify_params();
4250 if (op_ret < 0) {
4251 return;
4252 }
4253
4254 if (s->iam_policy || ! s->iam_user_policies.empty() || !s->session_policies.empty()) {
4255 auto identity_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->iam_user_policies, s->env,
4256 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
4257 s->object->get_obj());
4258 if (identity_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
4259 op_ret = -EACCES;
4260 return;
4261 }
4262
4263 rgw::IAM::Effect e = Effect::Pass;
4264 rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal princ_type = rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other;
4265 if (s->iam_policy) {
4266 ARN obj_arn(s->object->get_obj());
4267 e = s->iam_policy->eval(s->env, *s->auth.identity,
4268 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
4269 obj_arn,
4270 princ_type);
4271 }
4272 if (e == Effect::Deny) {
4273 op_ret = -EACCES;
4274 return;
4275 }
4276
4277 if (!s->session_policies.empty()) {
4278 auto session_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->session_policies, s->env,
4279 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
4280 s->object->get_obj());
4281 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
4282 op_ret = -EACCES;
4283 return;
4284 }
4285 if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Role) {
4286 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus intersection of session policy and bucket policy
4287 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) ||
4288 (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && e == Effect::Allow)) {
4289 op_ret = 0;
4290 return;
4291 }
4292 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Session) {
4293 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus bucket policy
4294 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) || e == Effect::Allow) {
4295 op_ret = 0;
4296 return;
4297 }
4298 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other) {// there was no match in the bucket policy
4299 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) {
4300 op_ret = 0;
4301 return;
4302 }
4303 }
4304 op_ret = -EACCES;
4305 return;
4306 }
4307 if (identity_policy_res == Effect::Pass && e == Effect::Pass && !verify_bucket_permission_no_policy(this, s, RGW_PERM_WRITE)) {
4308 op_ret = -EACCES;
4309 return;
4310 }
4311 } else if (!verify_bucket_permission_no_policy(this, s, RGW_PERM_WRITE)) {
4312 op_ret = -EACCES;
4313 return;
4314 }
4315
4316 // make reservation for notification if needed
4317 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Notification> res
4318 = store->get_notification(s->object.get(), s->src_object.get(), s, rgw::notify::ObjectCreatedPost);
4319 op_ret = res->publish_reserve(this);
4320 if (op_ret < 0) {
4321 return;
4322 }
4323
4324 /* Start iteration over data fields. It's necessary as Swift's FormPost
4325 * is capable to handle multiple files in single form. */
4326 do {
4327 char calc_md5[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE * 2 + 1];
4328 unsigned char m[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE];
4329 MD5 hash;
4330 // Allow use of MD5 digest in FIPS mode for non-cryptographic purposes
4331 hash.SetFlags(EVP_MD_CTX_FLAG_NON_FIPS_ALLOW);
4332 ceph::buffer::list bl, aclbl;
4333 int len = 0;
4334
4335 op_ret = s->bucket->check_quota(this, user_quota, bucket_quota, s->content_length, y);
4336 if (op_ret < 0) {
4337 return;
4338 }
4339
4340 if (supplied_md5_b64) {
4341 char supplied_md5_bin[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE + 1];
4342 ldpp_dout(this, 15) << "supplied_md5_b64=" << supplied_md5_b64 << dendl;
4343 op_ret = ceph_unarmor(supplied_md5_bin, &supplied_md5_bin[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE + 1],
4344 supplied_md5_b64, supplied_md5_b64 + strlen(supplied_md5_b64));
4345 ldpp_dout(this, 15) << "ceph_armor ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
4346 if (op_ret != CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE) {
4347 op_ret = -ERR_INVALID_DIGEST;
4348 return;
4349 }
4350
4351 buf_to_hex((const unsigned char *)supplied_md5_bin, CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE, supplied_md5);
4352 ldpp_dout(this, 15) << "supplied_md5=" << supplied_md5 << dendl;
4353 }
4354
4355 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Object> obj =
4356 s->bucket->get_object(rgw_obj_key(get_current_filename()));
4357 if (s->bucket->versioning_enabled()) {
4358 obj->gen_rand_obj_instance_name();
4359 }
4360
4361 auto aio = rgw::make_throttle(s->cct->_conf->rgw_put_obj_min_window_size,
4362 s->yield);
4363
4364 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Writer> processor;
4365 processor = store->get_atomic_writer(this, s->yield, std::move(obj),
4366 s->bucket_owner.get_id(), *s->obj_ctx,
4367 &s->dest_placement, 0, s->req_id);
4368 op_ret = processor->prepare(s->yield);
4369 if (op_ret < 0) {
4370 return;
4371 }
4372
4373 /* No filters by default. */
4374 rgw::sal::DataProcessor *filter = processor.get();
4375
4376 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::DataProcessor> encrypt;
4377 op_ret = get_encrypt_filter(&encrypt, filter);
4378 if (op_ret < 0) {
4379 return;
4380 }
4381 if (encrypt != nullptr) {
4382 filter = encrypt.get();
4383 } else {
4384 const auto& compression_type = store->get_zone()->get_params().get_compression_type(
4385 s->dest_placement);
4386 if (compression_type != "none") {
4387 plugin = Compressor::create(s->cct, compression_type);
4388 if (!plugin) {
4389 ldpp_dout(this, 1) << "Cannot load plugin for compression type "
4390 << compression_type << dendl;
4391 } else {
4392 compressor.emplace(s->cct, plugin, filter);
4393 filter = &*compressor;
4394 }
4395 }
4396 }
4397
4398 bool again;
4399 do {
4400 ceph::bufferlist data;
4401 len = get_data(data, again);
4402
4403 if (len < 0) {
4404 op_ret = len;
4405 return;
4406 }
4407
4408 if (!len) {
4409 break;
4410 }
4411
4412 hash.Update((const unsigned char *)data.c_str(), data.length());
4413 op_ret = filter->process(std::move(data), ofs);
4414 if (op_ret < 0) {
4415 return;
4416 }
4417
4418 ofs += len;
4419
4420 if (ofs > max_len) {
4421 op_ret = -ERR_TOO_LARGE;
4422 return;
4423 }
4424 } while (again);
4425
4426 // flush
4427 op_ret = filter->process({}, ofs);
4428 if (op_ret < 0) {
4429 return;
4430 }
4431
4432 if (len < min_len) {
4433 op_ret = -ERR_TOO_SMALL;
4434 return;
4435 }
4436
4437 s->obj_size = ofs;
4438 s->object->set_obj_size(ofs);
4439
4440
4441 op_ret = s->bucket->check_quota(this, user_quota, bucket_quota, s->obj_size, y);
4442 if (op_ret < 0) {
4443 return;
4444 }
4445
4446 hash.Final(m);
4447 buf_to_hex(m, CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE, calc_md5);
4448
4449 etag = calc_md5;
4450
4451 if (supplied_md5_b64 && strcmp(calc_md5, supplied_md5)) {
4452 op_ret = -ERR_BAD_DIGEST;
4453 return;
4454 }
4455
4456 bl.append(etag.c_str(), etag.size());
4457 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_ETAG, std::move(bl));
4458
4459 policy.encode(aclbl);
4460 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_ACL, std::move(aclbl));
4461
4462 const std::string content_type = get_current_content_type();
4463 if (! content_type.empty()) {
4464 ceph::bufferlist ct_bl;
4465 ct_bl.append(content_type.c_str(), content_type.size() + 1);
4466 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_CONTENT_TYPE, std::move(ct_bl));
4467 }
4468
4469 if (compressor && compressor->is_compressed()) {
4470 ceph::bufferlist tmp;
4471 RGWCompressionInfo cs_info;
4472 cs_info.compression_type = plugin->get_type_name();
4473 cs_info.orig_size = s->obj_size;
4474 cs_info.compressor_message = compressor->get_compressor_message();
4475 cs_info.blocks = move(compressor->get_compression_blocks());
4476 encode(cs_info, tmp);
4477 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_COMPRESSION, std::move(tmp));
4478 }
4479
4480 op_ret = processor->complete(s->obj_size, etag, nullptr, real_time(), attrs,
4481 (delete_at ? *delete_at : real_time()),
4482 nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr,
4483 s->yield);
4484 if (op_ret < 0) {
4485 return;
4486 }
4487 } while (is_next_file_to_upload());
4488
4489 // send request to notification manager
4490 int ret = res->publish_commit(this, ofs, s->object->get_mtime(), etag, s->object->get_instance());
4491 if (ret < 0) {
4492 ldpp_dout(this, 1) << "ERROR: publishing notification failed, with error: " << ret << dendl;
4493 // too late to rollback operation, hence op_ret is not set here
4494 }
4495}
4496
4497
4498void RGWPutMetadataAccount::filter_out_temp_url(map<string, bufferlist>& add_attrs,
4499 const set<string>& rmattr_names,
4500 map<int, string>& temp_url_keys)
4501{
4502 map<string, bufferlist>::iterator iter;
4503
4504 iter = add_attrs.find(RGW_ATTR_TEMPURL_KEY1);
4505 if (iter != add_attrs.end()) {
4506 temp_url_keys[0] = iter->second.c_str();
4507 add_attrs.erase(iter);
4508 }
4509
4510 iter = add_attrs.find(RGW_ATTR_TEMPURL_KEY2);
4511 if (iter != add_attrs.end()) {
4512 temp_url_keys[1] = iter->second.c_str();
4513 add_attrs.erase(iter);
4514 }
4515
4516 for (const string& name : rmattr_names) {
4517 if (name.compare(RGW_ATTR_TEMPURL_KEY1) == 0) {
4518 temp_url_keys[0] = string();
4519 }
4520 if (name.compare(RGW_ATTR_TEMPURL_KEY2) == 0) {
4521 temp_url_keys[1] = string();
4522 }
4523 }
4524}
4525
4526int RGWPutMetadataAccount::init_processing(optional_yield y)
4527{
4528 /* First, go to the base class. At the time of writing the method was
4529 * responsible only for initializing the quota. This isn't necessary
4530 * here as we are touching metadata only. I'm putting this call only
4531 * for the future. */
4532 op_ret = RGWOp::init_processing(y);
4533 if (op_ret < 0) {
4534 return op_ret;
4535 }
4536
4537 op_ret = get_params(y);
4538 if (op_ret < 0) {
4539 return op_ret;
4540 }
4541
4542 op_ret = s->user->read_attrs(this, y);
4543 if (op_ret < 0) {
4544 return op_ret;
4545 }
4546 orig_attrs = s->user->get_attrs();
4547
4548 if (has_policy) {
4549 bufferlist acl_bl;
4550 policy.encode(acl_bl);
4551 attrs.emplace(RGW_ATTR_ACL, std::move(acl_bl));
4552 }
4553
4554 op_ret = rgw_get_request_metadata(this, s->cct, s->info, attrs, false);
4555 if (op_ret < 0) {
4556 return op_ret;
4557 }
4558 prepare_add_del_attrs(orig_attrs, rmattr_names, attrs);
4559 populate_with_generic_attrs(s, attrs);
4560
4561 /* Try extract the TempURL-related stuff now to allow verify_permission
4562 * evaluate whether we need FULL_CONTROL or not. */
4563 filter_out_temp_url(attrs, rmattr_names, temp_url_keys);
4564
4565 /* The same with quota except a client needs to be reseller admin. */
4566 op_ret = filter_out_quota_info(attrs, rmattr_names, new_quota,
4567 &new_quota_extracted);
4568 if (op_ret < 0) {
4569 return op_ret;
4570 }
4571
4572 return 0;
4573}
4574
4575int RGWPutMetadataAccount::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
4576{
4577 if (s->auth.identity->is_anonymous()) {
4578 return -EACCES;
4579 }
4580
4581 if (!verify_user_permission_no_policy(this, s, RGW_PERM_WRITE)) {
4582 return -EACCES;
4583 }
4584
4585 /* Altering TempURL keys requires FULL_CONTROL. */
4586 if (!temp_url_keys.empty() && s->perm_mask != RGW_PERM_FULL_CONTROL) {
4587 return -EPERM;
4588 }
4589
4590 /* We are failing this intensionally to allow system user/reseller admin
4591 * override in rgw_process.cc. This is the way to specify a given RGWOp
4592 * expect extra privileges. */
4593 if (new_quota_extracted) {
4594 return -EACCES;
4595 }
4596
4597 return 0;
4598}
4599
4600void RGWPutMetadataAccount::execute(optional_yield y)
4601{
4602 /* Params have been extracted earlier. See init_processing(). */
4603 op_ret = s->user->load_user(this, y);
4604 if (op_ret < 0) {
4605 return;
4606 }
4607
4608 /* Handle the TempURL-related stuff. */
4609 if (!temp_url_keys.empty()) {
4610 for (auto& pair : temp_url_keys) {
4611 s->user->get_info().temp_url_keys[pair.first] = std::move(pair.second);
4612 }
4613 }
4614
4615 /* Handle the quota extracted at the verify_permission step. */
4616 if (new_quota_extracted) {
4617 s->user->get_info().user_quota = std::move(new_quota);
4618 }
4619
4620 /* We are passing here the current (old) user info to allow the function
4621 * optimize-out some operations. */
4622 s->user->set_attrs(attrs);
4623 op_ret = s->user->store_user(this, y, false, &s->user->get_info());
4624}

4626int RGWPutMetadataBucket::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
4627{
4628 if (!verify_bucket_permission_no_policy(this, s, RGW_PERM_WRITE)) {
4629 return -EACCES;
4630 }
4631
4632 return 0;
4633}
4634
4635void RGWPutMetadataBucket::pre_exec()
4636{
4637 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
4638}
4639
4640void RGWPutMetadataBucket::execute(optional_yield y)
4641{
4642 op_ret = get_params(y);
4643 if (op_ret < 0) {
4644 return;
4645 }
4646
4647 op_ret = rgw_get_request_metadata(this, s->cct, s->info, attrs, false);
4648 if (op_ret < 0) {
4649 return;
4650 }
4651
4652 if (!placement_rule.empty() &&
4653 placement_rule != s->bucket->get_placement_rule()) {
4654 op_ret = -EEXIST;
4655 return;
4656 }
4657
4658 op_ret = retry_raced_bucket_write(this, s->bucket.get(), [this] {
4659 /* Encode special metadata first as we're using std::map::emplace under
4660 * the hood. This method will add the new items only if the map doesn't
4661 * contain such keys yet. */
4662 if (has_policy) {
4663 if (s->dialect.compare("swift") == 0) {
4664 auto old_policy = \
4665 static_cast<RGWAccessControlPolicy_SWIFT*>(s->bucket_acl.get());
4666 auto new_policy = static_cast<RGWAccessControlPolicy_SWIFT*>(&policy);
4667 new_policy->filter_merge(policy_rw_mask, old_policy);
4668 policy = *new_policy;
4669 }
4670 buffer::list bl;
4671 policy.encode(bl);
4672 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_ACL, std::move(bl));
4673 }
4674
4675 if (has_cors) {
4676 buffer::list bl;
4677 cors_config.encode(bl);
4678 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_CORS, std::move(bl));
4679 }
4680
4681 /* It's supposed that following functions WILL NOT change any
4682 * special attributes (like RGW_ATTR_ACL) if they are already
4683 * present in attrs. */
4684 prepare_add_del_attrs(s->bucket_attrs, rmattr_names, attrs);
4685 populate_with_generic_attrs(s, attrs);
4686
4687 /* According to the Swift's behaviour and its container_quota
4688 * WSGI middleware implementation: anyone with write permissions
4689 * is able to set the bucket quota. This stays in contrast to
4690 * account quotas that can be set only by clients holding
4691 * reseller admin privileges. */
4692 op_ret = filter_out_quota_info(attrs, rmattr_names, s->bucket->get_info().quota);
4693 if (op_ret < 0) {
4694 return op_ret;
4695 }
4696
4697 if (swift_ver_location) {
4698 s->bucket->get_info().swift_ver_location = *swift_ver_location;
4699 s->bucket->get_info().swift_versioning = (!swift_ver_location->empty());
4700 }
4701
4702 /* Web site of Swift API. */
4703 filter_out_website(attrs, rmattr_names, s->bucket->get_info().website_conf);
4704 s->bucket->get_info().has_website = !s->bucket->get_info().website_conf.is_empty();
4705
4706 /* Setting attributes also stores the provided bucket info. Due
4707 * to this fact, the new quota settings can be serialized with
4708 * the same call. */
4709 op_ret = s->bucket->merge_and_store_attrs(this, attrs, s->yield);
4710 return op_ret;
4711 });
4712}

4716 // This looks to be something specific to Swift. We could add
4717 // operations like swift:PutMetadataObject to the Policy Engine.
4718 if (!verify_object_permission_no_policy(this, s, RGW_PERM_WRITE)) {
4719 return -EACCES;
4720 }
4721
4722 return 0;
