4729
4730void RGWPutMetadataObject::execute(optional_yield y)
4731{
4732 rgw_obj target_obj;
4733 rgw::sal::Attrs attrs, rmattrs;
4734
4735 s->object->set_atomic(s->obj_ctx);
4736
4737 op_ret = get_params(y);
4738 if (op_ret < 0) {
4739 return;
4740 }
4741
4742 op_ret = rgw_get_request_metadata(this, s->cct, s->info, attrs);
4743 if (op_ret < 0) {
4744 return;
4745 }
4746
4747 /* check if obj exists, read orig attrs */
4748 op_ret = s->object->get_obj_attrs(s->obj_ctx, s->yield, s, &target_obj);
4749 if (op_ret < 0) {
4750 return;
4751 }
4752
4753 /* Check whether the object has expired. Swift API documentation
4754 * stands that we should return 404 Not Found in such case. */
4755 if (need_object_expiration() && s->object->is_expired()) {
4756 op_ret = -ENOENT;
4757 return;
4758 }
4759
4760 /* Filter currently existing attributes. */
4761 prepare_add_del_attrs(s->object->get_attrs(), attrs, rmattrs);
4762 populate_with_generic_attrs(s, attrs);
4763 encode_delete_at_attr(delete_at, attrs);
4764
4765 if (dlo_manifest) {
4766 op_ret = encode_dlo_manifest_attr(dlo_manifest, attrs);
4767 if (op_ret < 0) {
4768 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "bad user manifest: " << dlo_manifest << dendl;
4769 return;
4770 }
4771 }
4772
4773 op_ret = s->object->set_obj_attrs(this, s->obj_ctx, &attrs, &rmattrs, s->yield, &target_obj);
4774}
4775
4776int RGWDeleteObj::handle_slo_manifest(bufferlist& bl, optional_yield y)
4777{
4778 RGWSLOInfo slo_info;
4779 auto bliter = bl.cbegin();
4780 try {
4781 decode(slo_info, bliter);
4782 } catch (buffer::error& err) {
4783 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: failed to decode slo manifest" << dendl;
4784 return -EIO;
4785 }
4786
4787 try {
4788 deleter = std::unique_ptr<RGWBulkDelete::Deleter>(\
4789 new RGWBulkDelete::Deleter(this, store, s));
4790 } catch (const std::bad_alloc&) {
4791 return -ENOMEM;
4792 }
4793
4794 list<RGWBulkDelete::acct_path_t> items;
4795 for (const auto& iter : slo_info.entries) {
4796 const string& path_str = iter.path;
4797
4798 const size_t sep_pos = path_str.find('/', 1 /* skip first slash */);
4799 if (std::string_view::npos == sep_pos) {
4800 return -EINVAL;
4801 }
4802
4803 RGWBulkDelete::acct_path_t path;
4804
4805 path.bucket_name = url_decode(path_str.substr(1, sep_pos - 1));
4806 path.obj_key = url_decode(path_str.substr(sep_pos + 1));
4807
4808 items.push_back(path);
4809 }
4810
4811 /* Request removal of the manifest object itself. */
4812 RGWBulkDelete::acct_path_t path;
4813 path.bucket_name = s->bucket_name;
4814 path.obj_key = s->object->get_key();
4815 items.push_back(path);
4816
4817 int ret = deleter->delete_chunk(items, y);
4818 if (ret < 0) {
4819 return ret;
4820 }
4821
4822 return 0;
4823}
4824
4825int RGWDeleteObj::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
4826{
4827 int op_ret = get_params(y);
4828 if (op_ret) {
4829 return op_ret;
4830 }
4831
4832 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s);
4833 if (has_s3_existing_tag || has_s3_resource_tag)
4834 rgw_iam_add_objtags(this, s, has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag);
4835
4836 if (s->iam_policy || ! s->iam_user_policies.empty() || ! s->session_policies.empty()) {
4837 if (s->bucket->get_info().obj_lock_enabled() && bypass_governance_mode) {
4838 auto r = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->iam_user_policies, s->env,
4839 rgw::IAM::s3BypassGovernanceRetention, ARN(s->bucket->get_key(), s->object->get_name()));
4840 if (r == Effect::Deny) {
4841 bypass_perm = false;
4842 } else if (r == Effect::Pass && s->iam_policy) {
4843 ARN obj_arn(ARN(s->bucket->get_key(), s->object->get_name()));
4844 r = s->iam_policy->eval(s->env, *s->auth.identity, rgw::IAM::s3BypassGovernanceRetention, obj_arn);
4845 if (r == Effect::Deny) {
4846 bypass_perm = false;
4847 }
4848 } else if (r == Effect::Pass && !s->session_policies.empty()) {
4849 r = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->session_policies, s->env,
4850 rgw::IAM::s3BypassGovernanceRetention, ARN(s->bucket->get_key(), s->object->get_name()));
4851 if (r == Effect::Deny) {
4852 bypass_perm = false;
4853 }
4854 }
4855 }
4856 auto identity_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->iam_user_policies, s->env,
4857 s->object->get_instance().empty() ?
4858 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObject :
4859 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObjectVersion,
4860 ARN(s->bucket->get_key(), s->object->get_name()));
4861 if (identity_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
4862 return -EACCES;
4863 }
4864
4865 rgw::IAM::Effect r = Effect::Pass;
4866 rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal princ_type = rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other;
4867 ARN obj_arn(ARN(s->bucket->get_key(), s->object->get_name()));
4868 if (s->iam_policy) {
4869 r = s->iam_policy->eval(s->env, *s->auth.identity,
4870 s->object->get_instance().empty() ?
4871 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObject :
4872 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObjectVersion,
4873 obj_arn,
4874 princ_type);
4875 }
4876 if (r == Effect::Deny)
4877 return -EACCES;
4878
4879 if (!s->session_policies.empty()) {
4880 auto session_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->session_policies, s->env,
4881 s->object->get_instance().empty() ?
4882 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObject :
4883 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObjectVersion,
4884 obj_arn);
4885 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
4886 return -EACCES;
4887 }
4888 if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Role) {
4889 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus intersection of session policy and bucket policy
4890 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) ||
4891 (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && r == Effect::Allow)) {
4892 return 0;
4893 }
4894 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Session) {
4895 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus bucket policy
4896 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) || r == Effect::Allow) {
4897 return 0;
4898 }
4899 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other) {// there was no match in the bucket policy
4900 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) {
4901 return 0;
4902 }
4903 }
4904 return -EACCES;
4905 }
4906 if (r == Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow)
4907 return 0;
4908 }
4909
4910 if (!verify_bucket_permission_no_policy(this, s, RGW_PERM_WRITE)) {
4911 return -EACCES;
4912 }
4913
4914 if (s->bucket->get_info().mfa_enabled() &&
4915 !s->object->get_instance().empty() &&
4916 !s->mfa_verified) {
4917 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << "NOTICE: object delete request with a versioned object, mfa auth not provided" << dendl;
4918 return -ERR_MFA_REQUIRED;
4919 }
4920
4921 return 0;
4922}
4923
4924void RGWDeleteObj::pre_exec()
4925{
4926 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
4927}
4928
4929void RGWDeleteObj::execute(optional_yield y)
4930{
4931 if (!s->bucket_exists) {
4932 op_ret = -ERR_NO_SUCH_BUCKET;
4933 return;
4934 }
4935
4936 if (!rgw::sal::Object::empty(s->object.get())) {
4937 uint64_t obj_size = 0;
4938 std::string etag;
4939 RGWObjectCtx* obj_ctx = static_cast<RGWObjectCtx *>(s->obj_ctx);
4940 {
4941 RGWObjState* astate = nullptr;
4942 bool check_obj_lock = s->object->have_instance() && s->bucket->get_info().obj_lock_enabled();
4943
4944 op_ret = s->object->get_obj_state(this, obj_ctx, &astate, s->yield, true);
4945 if (op_ret < 0) {
4946 if (need_object_expiration() || multipart_delete) {
4947 return;
4948 }
4949
4950 if (check_obj_lock) {
4951 /* check if obj exists, read orig attrs */
4952 if (op_ret == -ENOENT) {
4953 /* object maybe delete_marker, skip check_obj_lock*/
4954 check_obj_lock = false;
4955 } else {
4956 return;
4957 }
4958 }
4959 } else {
4960 obj_size = astate->size;
4961 etag = astate->attrset[RGW_ATTR_ETAG].to_str();
4962 }
4963
4964 // ignore return value from get_obj_attrs in all other cases
4965 op_ret = 0;
4966
4967 if (check_obj_lock) {
4968 ceph_assert(astate);
4969 int object_lock_response = verify_object_lock(this, astate->attrset, bypass_perm, bypass_governance_mode);
4970 if (object_lock_response != 0) {
4971 op_ret = object_lock_response;
4972 if (op_ret == -EACCES) {
4973 s->err.message = "forbidden by object lock";
4974 }
4975 return;
4976 }
4977 }
4978
4979 if (multipart_delete) {
4980 if (!astate) {
4981 op_ret = -ERR_NOT_SLO_MANIFEST;
4982 return;
4983 }
4984
4985 const auto slo_attr = astate->attrset.find(RGW_ATTR_SLO_MANIFEST);
4986
4987 if (slo_attr != astate->attrset.end()) {
4988 op_ret = handle_slo_manifest(slo_attr->second, y);
4989 if (op_ret < 0) {
4990 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: failed to handle slo manifest ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
4991 }
4992 } else {
4993 op_ret = -ERR_NOT_SLO_MANIFEST;
4994 }
4995
4996 return;
4997 }
4998 }
4999
5000 // make reservation for notification if needed
5001 const auto versioned_object = s->bucket->versioning_enabled();
5002 const auto event_type = versioned_object &&
5003 s->object->get_instance().empty() ?
5004 rgw::notify::ObjectRemovedDeleteMarkerCreated :
5005 rgw::notify::ObjectRemovedDelete;
5006 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Notification> res
5007 = store->get_notification(s->object.get(), s->src_object.get(), s,
5008 event_type);
5009 op_ret = res->publish_reserve(this);
5010 if (op_ret < 0) {
5011 return;
5012 }
5013
5014 s->object->set_atomic(s->obj_ctx);
5015
5016 bool ver_restored = false;
5017 op_ret = s->object->swift_versioning_restore(s->obj_ctx, ver_restored, this);
5018 if (op_ret < 0) {
5019 return;
5020 }
5021
5022 if (!ver_restored) {
5023 uint64_t epoch = 0;
5024
5025 /* Swift's versioning mechanism hasn't found any previous version of
5026 * the object that could be restored. This means we should proceed
5027 * with the regular delete path. */
5028 op_ret = get_system_versioning_params(s, &epoch, &version_id);
5029 if (op_ret < 0) {
5030 return;
5031 }
5032
5033 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Object::DeleteOp> del_op = s->object->get_delete_op(obj_ctx);
5034 del_op->params.obj_owner = s->owner;
5035 del_op->params.bucket_owner = s->bucket_owner;
5036 del_op->params.versioning_status = s->bucket->get_info().versioning_status();
5037 del_op->params.unmod_since = unmod_since;
5038 del_op->params.high_precision_time = s->system_request;
5039 del_op->params.olh_epoch = epoch;
5040 del_op->params.marker_version_id = version_id;
5041
5042 op_ret = del_op->delete_obj(this, y);
5043 if (op_ret >= 0) {
5044 delete_marker = del_op->result.delete_marker;
5045 version_id = del_op->result.version_id;
5046 }
5047
5048 /* Check whether the object has expired. Swift API documentation
5049 * stands that we should return 404 Not Found in such case. */
5050 if (need_object_expiration() && s->object->is_expired()) {
5051 op_ret = -ENOENT;
5052 return;
5053 }
5054 }
5055
5056 if (op_ret == -ECANCELED) {
5057 op_ret = 0;
5058 }
5059 if (op_ret == -ERR_PRECONDITION_FAILED && no_precondition_error) {
5060 op_ret = 0;
5061 }
5062
5063 // send request to notification manager
5064 int ret = res->publish_commit(this, obj_size, ceph::real_clock::now(), etag, version_id);
5065 if (ret < 0) {
5066 ldpp_dout(this, 1) << "ERROR: publishing notification failed, with error: " << ret << dendl;
5067 // too late to rollback operation, hence op_ret is not set here
5068 }
5069 } else {
5070 op_ret = -EINVAL;
5071 }
5072}
5073
5074bool RGWCopyObj::parse_copy_location(const std::string_view& url_src,
5075 string& bucket_name,
5076 rgw_obj_key& key,
5077 req_state* s)
5078{
5079 std::string_view name_str;
5080 std::string_view params_str;
5081
5082 // search for ? before url-decoding so we don't accidentally match %3F
5083 size_t pos = url_src.find('?');
5084 if (pos == string::npos) {
5085 name_str = url_src;
5086 } else {
5087 name_str = url_src.substr(0, pos);
5088 params_str = url_src.substr(pos + 1);
5089 }
5090
5091 if (name_str[0] == '/') // trim leading slash
5092 name_str.remove_prefix(1);
5093
5094 std::string dec_src = url_decode(name_str);
5095
5096 pos = dec_src.find('/');
5097 if (pos == string::npos)
5098 return false;
5099
5100 bucket_name = dec_src.substr(0, pos);
5101 key.name = dec_src.substr(pos + 1);
5102
5103 if (key.name.empty()) {
5104 return false;
5105 }
5106
5107 if (! params_str.empty()) {
5108 RGWHTTPArgs args;
5109 args.set(std::string(params_str));
5110 args.parse(s);
5111
5112 key.instance = args.get("versionId", NULL);
5113 }
5114
5115 return true;
5116}
5117
5118int RGWCopyObj::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
5119{
5120 RGWAccessControlPolicy src_acl(s->cct);
5121 boost::optional<Policy> src_policy;
5122 op_ret = get_params(y);
5123 if (op_ret < 0)
5124 return op_ret;
5125
5126 op_ret = get_system_versioning_params(s, &olh_epoch, &version_id);
5127 if (op_ret < 0) {
5128 return op_ret;
5129 }
5130
5131 op_ret = store->get_bucket(this, s->user.get(),
5132 rgw_bucket(src_tenant_name,
5133 src_bucket_name,
5134 s->bucket_instance_id),
5135 &src_bucket, y);
5136 if (op_ret < 0) {
5137 if (op_ret == -ENOENT) {
5138 op_ret = -ERR_NO_SUCH_BUCKET;
5139 }
5140 return op_ret;
5141 }
5142
5143 /* This is the only place the bucket is set on src_object */
5144 s->src_object->set_bucket(src_bucket.get());
5145 /* get buckets info (source and dest) */
5146 if (s->local_source && source_zone.empty()) {
5147 s->src_object->set_atomic(s->obj_ctx);
5148 s->src_object->set_prefetch_data(s->obj_ctx);
5149
5150 rgw_placement_rule src_placement;
5151
5152 /* check source object permissions */
5153 op_ret = read_obj_policy(this, store, s, src_bucket->get_info(), src_bucket->get_attrs(), &src_acl, &src_placement.storage_class,
5154 src_policy, src_bucket.get(), s->src_object.get(), y);
5155 if (op_ret < 0) {
5156 return op_ret;
5157 }
5158
5159 /* follow up on previous checks that required reading source object head */
5160 if (need_to_check_storage_class) {
5161 src_placement.inherit_from(src_bucket->get_placement_rule());
5162
5163 op_ret = check_storage_class(src_placement);
5164 if (op_ret < 0) {
5165 return op_ret;
5166 }
5167 }
5168
5169 /* admin request overrides permission checks */
5170 if (!s->auth.identity->is_admin_of(src_acl.get_owner().get_id())) {
5171 if (src_policy || ! s->iam_user_policies.empty() || !s->session_policies.empty()) {
5172 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, src_policy, s->iam_user_policies, s->session_policies);
5173 if (has_s3_existing_tag || has_s3_resource_tag)
5174 rgw_iam_add_objtags(this, s, s->src_object.get(), has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag);
5175
5176 ARN obj_arn(s->src_object->get_obj());
5177 auto identity_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->iam_user_policies, s->env,
5178 s->src_object->get_instance().empty() ?
5179 rgw::IAM::s3GetObject :
5180 rgw::IAM::s3GetObjectVersion,
5181 obj_arn);
5182 if (identity_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
5183 return -EACCES;
5184 }
5185 auto e = Effect::Pass;
5186 rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal princ_type = rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other;
5187 if (src_policy) {
5188 e = src_policy->eval(s->env, *s->auth.identity,
5189 s->src_object->get_instance().empty() ?
5190 rgw::IAM::s3GetObject :
5191 rgw::IAM::s3GetObjectVersion,
5192 obj_arn,
5193 princ_type);
5194 }
5195 if (e == Effect::Deny) {
5196 return -EACCES;
5197 }
5198 if (!s->session_policies.empty()) {
5199 auto session_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->session_policies, s->env,
5200 s->src_object->get_instance().empty() ?
5201 rgw::IAM::s3GetObject :
5202 rgw::IAM::s3GetObjectVersion,
5203 obj_arn);
5204 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
5205 return -EACCES;
5206 }
5207 if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Role) {
5208 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus intersection of session policy and bucket policy
5209 if ((session_policy_res != Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res != Effect::Allow) &&
5210 (session_policy_res != Effect::Allow || e != Effect::Allow)) {
5211 return -EACCES;
5212 }
5213 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Session) {
5214 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus bucket policy
5215 if ((session_policy_res != Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res != Effect::Allow) && e != Effect::Allow) {
5216 return -EACCES;
5217 }
5218 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other) {// there was no match in the bucket policy
5219 if (session_policy_res != Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res != Effect::Allow) {
5220 return -EACCES;
5221 }
5222 }
5223 }
5224 if (identity_policy_res == Effect::Pass && e == Effect::Pass &&
5225 !src_acl.verify_permission(this, *s->auth.identity, s->perm_mask,
5226 RGW_PERM_READ)) {
5227 return -EACCES;
5228 }
5229 //remove src object tags as it may interfere with policy evaluation of destination obj
5230 if (has_s3_existing_tag || has_s3_resource_tag)
5231 rgw_iam_remove_objtags(this, s, s->src_object.get(), has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag);
5232
5233 } else if (!src_acl.verify_permission(this, *s->auth.identity,
5234 s->perm_mask,
5235 RGW_PERM_READ)) {
5236 return -EACCES;
5237 }
5238 }
5239 }
5240
5241 RGWAccessControlPolicy dest_bucket_policy(s->cct);
5242
5243 if (src_bucket_name.compare(dest_bucket_name) == 0) { /* will only happen if s->local_source
5244 or intra region sync */
5245 dest_bucket = src_bucket->clone();
5246 } else {
5247 op_ret = store->get_bucket(this, s->user.get(), dest_tenant_name, dest_bucket_name, &dest_bucket, y);
5248 if (op_ret < 0) {
5249 if (op_ret == -ENOENT) {
5250 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: Destination Bucket not found for user: " << s->user->get_id().to_str() << dendl;
5251 op_ret = -ERR_NO_SUCH_BUCKET;
5252 }
5253 return op_ret;
5254 }
5255 }
5256
5257 dest_object = dest_bucket->get_object(rgw_obj_key(dest_obj_name));
5258 dest_object->set_atomic(s->obj_ctx);
5259
5260 /* check dest bucket permissions */
5261 op_ret = read_bucket_policy(this, store, s, dest_bucket->get_info(),
5262 dest_bucket->get_attrs(),
5263 &dest_bucket_policy, dest_bucket->get_key(), y);
5264 if (op_ret < 0) {
5265 return op_ret;
5266 }
5267 auto dest_iam_policy = get_iam_policy_from_attr(s->cct, dest_bucket->get_attrs(), dest_bucket->get_tenant());
5268 /* admin request overrides permission checks */
5269 if (! s->auth.identity->is_admin_of(dest_policy.get_owner().get_id())){
5270 if (dest_iam_policy != boost::none || ! s->iam_user_policies.empty() || !s->session_policies.empty()) {
5271 //Add destination bucket tags for authorization
5272 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, dest_iam_policy, s->iam_user_policies, s->session_policies);
5273 if (has_s3_resource_tag)
5274 rgw_iam_add_buckettags(this, s, dest_bucket.get());
5275
5276 rgw_add_to_iam_environment(s->env, "s3:x-amz-copy-source", copy_source);
5277 if (md_directive)
5278 rgw_add_to_iam_environment(s->env, "s3:x-amz-metadata-directive",
5279 *md_directive);
5280
5281 ARN obj_arn(dest_object->get_obj());
5282 auto identity_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->iam_user_policies,
5283 s->env,
5284 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
5285 obj_arn);
5286 if (identity_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
5287 return -EACCES;
5288 }
5289 auto e = Effect::Pass;
5290 rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal princ_type = rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other;
5291 if (dest_iam_policy) {
5292 e = dest_iam_policy->eval(s->env, *s->auth.identity,
5293 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
5294 obj_arn,
5295 princ_type);
5296 }
5297 if (e == Effect::Deny) {
5298 return -EACCES;
5299 }
5300 if (!s->session_policies.empty()) {
5301 auto session_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->session_policies, s->env, rgw::IAM::s3PutObject, obj_arn);
5302 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
5303 return false;
5304 }
5305 if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Role) {
5306 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus intersection of session policy and bucket policy
5307 if ((session_policy_res != Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res != Effect::Allow) &&
5308 (session_policy_res != Effect::Allow || e == Effect::Allow)) {
5309 return -EACCES;
5310 }
5311 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Session) {
5312 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus bucket policy
5313 if ((session_policy_res != Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res != Effect::Allow) && e != Effect::Allow) {
5314 return -EACCES;
5315 }
5316 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other) {// there was no match in the bucket policy
5317 if (session_policy_res != Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res != Effect::Allow) {
5318 return -EACCES;
5319 }
5320 }
5321 }
5322 if (identity_policy_res == Effect::Pass && e == Effect::Pass &&
5323 ! dest_bucket_policy.verify_permission(this,
5324 *s->auth.identity,
5325 s->perm_mask,
5326 RGW_PERM_WRITE)){
5327 return -EACCES;
5328 }
5329 } else if (! dest_bucket_policy.verify_permission(this, *s->auth.identity, s->perm_mask,
5330 RGW_PERM_WRITE)) {
5331 return -EACCES;
5332 }
5333
5334 }
5335
5336 op_ret = init_dest_policy();
5337 if (op_ret < 0) {
5338 return op_ret;
5339 }
5340
5341 return 0;
5342}
5343
5344
5345int RGWCopyObj::init_common()
5346{
5347 if (if_mod) {
5348 if (parse_time(if_mod, &mod_time) < 0) {
5349 op_ret = -EINVAL;
5350 return op_ret;
5351 }
5352 mod_ptr = &mod_time;
5353 }
5354
5355 if (if_unmod) {
5356 if (parse_time(if_unmod, &unmod_time) < 0) {
5357 op_ret = -EINVAL;
5358 return op_ret;
5359 }
5360 unmod_ptr = &unmod_time;
5361 }
5362
5363 bufferlist aclbl;
5364 dest_policy.encode(aclbl);
5365 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_ACL, std::move(aclbl));
5366
5367 op_ret = rgw_get_request_metadata(this, s->cct, s->info, attrs);
5368 if (op_ret < 0) {
5369 return op_ret;
5370 }
5371 populate_with_generic_attrs(s, attrs);
5372
5373 return 0;
5374}
5375
5376static void copy_obj_progress_cb(off_t ofs, void *param)
5377{
5378 RGWCopyObj *op = static_cast<RGWCopyObj *>(param);
5379 op->progress_cb(ofs);
5380}
5381
5382void RGWCopyObj::progress_cb(off_t ofs)
5383{
5384 if (!s->cct->_conf->rgw_copy_obj_progress)
5385 return;
5386
5387 if (ofs - last_ofs <
5388 static_cast<off_t>(s->cct->_conf->rgw_copy_obj_progress_every_bytes)) {
5389 return;
5390 }
5391
5392 send_partial_response(ofs);
5393
5394 last_ofs = ofs;
5395}
5396
5397void RGWCopyObj::pre_exec()
5398{
5399 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
5400}
5401
5402void RGWCopyObj::execute(optional_yield y)
5403{
5404 if (init_common() < 0)
5405 return;
5406
5407 // make reservation for notification if needed
5408 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Notification> res
5409 = store->get_notification(
5410 s->object.get(), s->src_object.get(),
5411 s, rgw::notify::ObjectCreatedCopy);
5412 op_ret = res->publish_reserve(this);
5413 if (op_ret < 0) {
5414 return;
5415 }
5416
5417 if ( ! version_id.empty()) {
5418 dest_object->set_instance(version_id);
5419 } else if (dest_bucket->versioning_enabled()) {
5420 dest_object->gen_rand_obj_instance_name();
5421 }
5422
5423 s->src_object->set_atomic(s->obj_ctx);
5424 dest_object->set_atomic(s->obj_ctx);
5425
5426 encode_delete_at_attr(delete_at, attrs);
5427
5428 if (obj_retention) {
5429 bufferlist obj_retention_bl;
5430 obj_retention->encode(obj_retention_bl);
5431 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_OBJECT_RETENTION, std::move(obj_retention_bl));
5432 }
5433 if (obj_legal_hold) {
5434 bufferlist obj_legal_hold_bl;
5435 obj_legal_hold->encode(obj_legal_hold_bl);
5436 emplace_attr(RGW_ATTR_OBJECT_LEGAL_HOLD, std::move(obj_legal_hold_bl));
5437 }
5438
5439 uint64_t obj_size = 0;
5440 {
5441 // get src object size (cached in obj_ctx from verify_permission())
5442 RGWObjState* astate = nullptr;
5443 op_ret = s->src_object->get_obj_state(this, s->obj_ctx, &astate, s->yield, true);
5444 if (op_ret < 0) {
5445 return;
5446 }
5447
5448 /* Check if the src object is cloud-tiered */
5449 bufferlist bl;
5450 if (astate->get_attr(RGW_ATTR_MANIFEST, bl)) {
5451 RGWObjManifest m;
5452 decode(m, bl);
5453 if (m.get_tier_type() == "cloud-s3") {
5454 op_ret = -ERR_INVALID_OBJECT_STATE;
5455 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: Cannot copy cloud tiered object. Failing with "
5456 << op_ret << dendl;
5457 return;
5458 }
5459 }
5460
5461 obj_size = astate->size;
5462
5463 if (!s->system_request) { // no quota enforcement for system requests
5464 if (astate->accounted_size > static_cast<size_t>(s->cct->_conf->rgw_max_put_size)) {
5465 op_ret = -ERR_TOO_LARGE;
5466 return;
5467 }
5468 // enforce quota against the destination bucket owner
5469 op_ret = dest_bucket->check_quota(this, user_quota, bucket_quota,
5470 astate->accounted_size, y);
5471 if (op_ret < 0) {
5472 return;
5473 }
5474 }
5475 }
5476
5477 bool high_precision_time = (s->system_request);
5478
5479 /* Handle object versioning of Swift API. In case of copying to remote this
5480 * should fail gently (op_ret == 0) as the dst_obj will not exist here. */
5481 op_ret = dest_object->swift_versioning_copy(s->obj_ctx, this, s->yield);
5482 if (op_ret < 0) {
5483 return;
5484 }
5485
5486 RGWObjectCtx& obj_ctx = *static_cast<RGWObjectCtx *>(s->obj_ctx);
5487 op_ret = s->src_object->copy_object(obj_ctx,
5488 s->user.get(),
5489 &s->info,
5490 source_zone,
5491 dest_object.get(),
5492 dest_bucket.get(),
5493 src_bucket.get(),
5494 s->dest_placement,
5495 &src_mtime,
5496 &mtime,
5497 mod_ptr,
5498 unmod_ptr,
5499 high_precision_time,
5500 if_match,
5501 if_nomatch,
5502 attrs_mod,
5503 copy_if_newer,
5504 attrs,
5505 RGWObjCategory::Main,
5506 olh_epoch,
5507 delete_at,
5508 (version_id.empty() ? NULL : &version_id),
5509 &s->req_id, /* use req_id as tag */
5510 &etag,
5511 copy_obj_progress_cb, (void *)this,
5512 this,
5513 s->yield);
5514
5515 // send request to notification manager
5516 int ret = res->publish_commit(this, obj_size, mtime, etag, dest_object->get_instance());
5517 if (ret < 0) {
5518 ldpp_dout(this, 1) << "ERROR: publishing notification failed, with error: " << ret << dendl;
5519 // too late to rollback operation, hence op_ret is not set here
5520 }
5521}
5522
5523int RGWGetACLs::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
5524{
5525 bool perm;
5526 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s);
5527 if (!rgw::sal::Object::empty(s->object.get())) {
5528 auto iam_action = s->object->get_instance().empty() ?
5529 rgw::IAM::s3GetObjectAcl :
5530 rgw::IAM::s3GetObjectVersionAcl;
5531 if (has_s3_existing_tag || has_s3_resource_tag)
5532 rgw_iam_add_objtags(this, s, has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag);
5533 perm = verify_object_permission(this, s, iam_action);
5534 } else {
5535 if (!s->bucket_exists) {
5536 return -ERR_NO_SUCH_BUCKET;
5537 }
5538 if (has_s3_resource_tag)
5539 rgw_iam_add_buckettags(this, s);
5540 perm = verify_bucket_permission(this, s, rgw::IAM::s3GetBucketAcl);
5541 }
5542 if (!perm)
5543 return -EACCES;
5544
5545 return 0;
5546}
5547
5548void RGWGetACLs::pre_exec()
5549{
5550 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
5551}

5553void RGWGetACLs::execute(optional_yield y)
5554{
5555 stringstream ss;
5556 RGWAccessControlPolicy* const acl = \
5557 (!rgw::sal::Object::empty(s->object.get()) ? s->object_acl.get() : s->bucket_acl.get());
5558 RGWAccessControlPolicy_S3* const s3policy = \
5559 static_cast<RGWAccessControlPolicy_S3*>(acl);
5560 s3policy->to_xml(ss);
5561 acls = ss.str();
5562}

5571
5572 rgw_add_grant_to_iam_environment(s->env, s);
5573 if (!rgw::sal::Object::empty(s->object.get())) {
5574 auto iam_action = s->object->get_instance().empty() ? rgw::IAM::s3PutObjectAcl : rgw::IAM::s3PutObjectVersionAcl;
5575 op_ret = rgw_iam_add_objtags(this, s, true, true);
5576 perm = verify_object_permission(this, s, iam_action);
5577 } else {
5578 op_ret = rgw_iam_add_buckettags(this, s);
5579 perm = verify_bucket_permission(this, s, rgw::IAM::s3PutBucketAcl);
5580 }
5581 if (!perm)
5582 return -EACCES;
5583
5584 return 0;
5585}

5648
5649void RGWPutACLs::execute(optional_yield y)
5650{
5651 bufferlist bl;
5652
5653 RGWAccessControlPolicy_S3 *policy = NULL;
5654 RGWACLXMLParser_S3 parser(s->cct);
5655 RGWAccessControlPolicy_S3 new_policy(s->cct);
5656 stringstream ss;
5657
5658 op_ret = 0; /* XXX redundant? */
5659
5660 if (!parser.init()) {
5661 op_ret = -EINVAL;
5662 return;
5663 }
5664
5665
5666 RGWAccessControlPolicy* const existing_policy = \
5667 (rgw::sal::Object::empty(s->object.get()) ? s->bucket_acl.get() : s->object_acl.get());
5668
5669 owner = existing_policy->get_owner();
5670
5671 op_ret = get_params(y);
5672 if (op_ret < 0) {
5673 if (op_ret == -ERANGE) {
5674 ldpp_dout(this, 4) << "The size of request xml data is larger than the max limitation, data size = "
5675 << s->length << dendl;
5676 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;
5677 s->err.message = "The XML you provided was larger than the maximum " +
5678 std::to_string(s->cct->_conf->rgw_max_put_param_size) +
5679 " bytes allowed.";
5680 }
5681 return;
5682 }
5683
5684 char* buf = data.c_str();
5685 ldpp_dout(this, 15) << "read len=" << data.length() << " data=" << (buf ? buf : "") << dendl;
5686
5687 if (!s->canned_acl.empty() && data.length() > 0) {
5688 op_ret = -EINVAL;
5689 return;
5690 }
5691
5692 if (!s->canned_acl.empty() || s->has_acl_header) {
5693 op_ret = get_policy_from_state(store, s, ss);
5694 if (op_ret < 0)
5695 return;
5696
5697 data.clear();
5698 data.append(ss.str());
5699 }
5700
5701 if (!parser.parse(data.c_str(), data.length(), 1)) {
5702 op_ret = -EINVAL;
5703 return;
5704 }
5705 policy = static_cast<RGWAccessControlPolicy_S3 *>(parser.find_first("AccessControlPolicy"));
5706 if (!policy) {
5707 op_ret = -EINVAL;
5708 return;
5709 }
5710
5711 const RGWAccessControlList& req_acl = policy->get_acl();
5712 const multimap<string, ACLGrant>& req_grant_map = req_acl.get_grant_map();
5713#define ACL_GRANTS_MAX_NUM 100
5714 int max_num = s->cct->_conf->rgw_acl_grants_max_num;
5715 if (max_num < 0) {
5716 max_num = ACL_GRANTS_MAX_NUM;
5717 }
5718
5719 int grants_num = req_grant_map.size();
5720 if (grants_num > max_num) {
5721 ldpp_dout(this, 4) << "An acl can have up to " << max_num
5722 << " grants, request acl grants num: " << grants_num << dendl;
5723 op_ret = -ERR_LIMIT_EXCEEDED;
5724 s->err.message = "The request is rejected, because the acl grants number you requested is larger than the maximum "
5725 + std::to_string(max_num)
5726 + " grants allowed in an acl.";
5727 return;
5728 }
5729
5730 // forward bucket acl requests to meta master zone
5731 if ((rgw::sal::Object::empty(s->object.get()))) {
5732 bufferlist in_data;
5733 // include acl data unless it was generated from a canned_acl
5734 if (s->canned_acl.empty()) {
5735 in_data.append(data);
5736 }
5737 op_ret = store->forward_request_to_master(this, s->user.get(), nullptr, in_data, nullptr, s->info, y);
5738 if (op_ret < 0) {
5739 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "forward_request_to_master returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
5740 return;
5741 }
5742 }
5743
5744 if (s->cct->_conf->subsys.should_gather<ceph_subsys_rgw, 15>()) {
5745 ldpp_dout(this, 15) << "Old AccessControlPolicy";
5746 policy->to_xml(*_dout);
5747 *_dout << dendl;
5748 }
5749
5750 op_ret = policy->rebuild(this, store, &owner, new_policy, s->err.message);
5751 if (op_ret < 0)
5752 return;
5753
5754 if (s->cct->_conf->subsys.should_gather<ceph_subsys_rgw, 15>()) {
5755 ldpp_dout(this, 15) << "New AccessControlPolicy:";
5756 new_policy.to_xml(*_dout);
5757 *_dout << dendl;
5758 }
5759
5760 if (s->bucket_access_conf &&
5761 s->bucket_access_conf->block_public_acls() &&
5762 new_policy.is_public(this)) {
5763 op_ret = -EACCES;
5764 return;
5765 }
5766 new_policy.encode(bl);
5767 map<string, bufferlist> attrs;
5768
5769 if (!rgw::sal::Object::empty(s->object.get())) {
5770 s->object->set_atomic(s->obj_ctx);
5771 //if instance is empty, we should modify the latest object
5772 op_ret = s->object->modify_obj_attrs(s->obj_ctx, RGW_ATTR_ACL, bl, s->yield, this);
5773 } else {
5774 map<string,bufferlist> attrs = s->bucket_attrs;
5775 attrs[RGW_ATTR_ACL] = bl;
5776 op_ret = s->bucket->merge_and_store_attrs(this, attrs, y);
5777 }
5778 if (op_ret == -ECANCELED) {
5779 op_ret = 0; /* lost a race, but it's ok because acls are immutable */
5780 }
5781}
5782
5783void RGWPutLC::execute(optional_yield y)
5784{
5785 bufferlist bl;
5786
5787 RGWLifecycleConfiguration_S3 config(s->cct);
5788 RGWXMLParser parser;
5789 RGWLifecycleConfiguration_S3 new_config(s->cct);
5790
5791 // amazon says that Content-MD5 is required for this op specifically, but MD5
5792 // is not a security primitive and FIPS mode makes it difficult to use. if the
5793 // client provides the header we'll try to verify its checksum, but the header
5794 // itself is no longer required
5795 std::optional<std::string> content_md5_bin;
5796
5797 content_md5 = s->info.env->get("HTTP_CONTENT_MD5");
5798 if (content_md5 != nullptr) {
5799 try {
5800 content_md5_bin = rgw::from_base64(std::string_view(content_md5));
5801 } catch (...) {
5802 s->err.message = "Request header Content-MD5 contains character "
5803 "that is not base64 encoded.";
5804 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << s->err.message << dendl;
5805 op_ret = -ERR_BAD_DIGEST;
5806 return;
5807 }
5808 }
5809
5810 if (!parser.init()) {
5811 op_ret = -EINVAL;
5812 return;
5813 }
5814
5815 op_ret = get_params(y);
5816 if (op_ret < 0)
5817 return;
5818
5819 char* buf = data.c_str();
5820 ldpp_dout(this, 15) << "read len=" << data.length() << " data=" << (buf ? buf : "") << dendl;
5821
5822 if (content_md5_bin) {
5823 MD5 data_hash;
5824 // Allow use of MD5 digest in FIPS mode for non-cryptographic purposes
5825 data_hash.SetFlags(EVP_MD_CTX_FLAG_NON_FIPS_ALLOW);
5826 unsigned char data_hash_res[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE];
5827 data_hash.Update(reinterpret_cast<const unsigned char*>(buf), data.length());
5828 data_hash.Final(data_hash_res);
5829
5830 if (memcmp(data_hash_res, content_md5_bin->c_str(), CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE) != 0) {
5831 op_ret = -ERR_BAD_DIGEST;
5832 s->err.message = "The Content-MD5 you specified did not match what we received.";
5833 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << s->err.message
5834 << " Specified content md5: " << content_md5
5835 << ", calculated content md5: " << data_hash_res
5836 << dendl;
5837 return;
5838 }
5839 }
5840
5841 if (!parser.parse(buf, data.length(), 1)) {
5842 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;
5843 return;
5844 }
5845
5846 try {
5847 RGWXMLDecoder::decode_xml("LifecycleConfiguration", config, &parser);
5848 } catch (RGWXMLDecoder::err& err) {
5849 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << "Bad lifecycle configuration: " << err << dendl;
5850 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;
5851 return;
5852 }
5853
5854 op_ret = config.rebuild(new_config);
5855 if (op_ret < 0)
5856 return;
5857
5858 if (s->cct->_conf->subsys.should_gather<ceph_subsys_rgw, 15>()) {
5859 XMLFormatter xf;
5860 new_config.dump_xml(&xf);
5861 stringstream ss;
5862 xf.flush(ss);
5863 ldpp_dout(this, 15) << "New LifecycleConfiguration:" << ss.str() << dendl;
5864 }
5865
5866 op_ret = store->forward_request_to_master(this, s->user.get(), nullptr, data, nullptr, s->info, y);
5867 if (op_ret < 0) {
5868 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "forward_request_to_master returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
5869 return;
5870 }
5871
5872 op_ret = store->get_rgwlc()->set_bucket_config(s->bucket.get(), s->bucket_attrs, &new_config);
5873 if (op_ret < 0) {
5874 return;
5875 }
5876 return;
5877}
5878
5879void RGWDeleteLC::execute(optional_yield y)
5880{
5881 bufferlist data;
5882 op_ret = store->forward_request_to_master(this, s->user.get(), nullptr, data, nullptr, s->info, y);
5883 if (op_ret < 0) {
5884 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "forward_request_to_master returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
5885 return;
5886 }
5887
5888 op_ret = store->get_rgwlc()->remove_bucket_config(s->bucket.get(), s->bucket_attrs);
5889 if (op_ret < 0) {
5890 return;
5891 }
5892 return;
5893}

5926void RGWPutCORS::execute(optional_yield y)
5927{
5928 rgw_raw_obj obj;
5929
5930 op_ret = get_params(y);
5931 if (op_ret < 0)
5932 return;
5933
5934 op_ret = store->forward_request_to_master(this, s->user.get(), nullptr, in_data, nullptr, s->info, y);
5935 if (op_ret < 0) {
5936 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "forward_request_to_master returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
5937 return;
5938 }
5939
5940 op_ret = retry_raced_bucket_write(this, s->bucket.get(), [this] {
5941 rgw::sal::Attrs attrs(s->bucket_attrs);
5942 attrs[RGW_ATTR_CORS] = cors_bl;
5943 return s->bucket->merge_and_store_attrs(this, attrs, s->yield);

5956
5957void RGWDeleteCORS::execute(optional_yield y)
5958{
5959 bufferlist data;
5960 op_ret = store->forward_request_to_master(this, s->user.get(), nullptr, data, nullptr, s->info, y);
5961 if (op_ret < 0) {
5962 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "forward_request_to_master returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
5963 return;
5964 }
5965
5966 op_ret = retry_raced_bucket_write(this, s->bucket.get(), [this] {
5967 op_ret = read_bucket_cors();
5968 if (op_ret < 0)
5969 return op_ret;
5970
5971 if (!cors_exist) {
5972 ldpp_dout(this, 2) << "No CORS configuration set yet for this bucket" << dendl;
5973 op_ret = -ENOENT;
5974 return op_ret;
5975 }
5976
5977 rgw::sal::Attrs attrs(s->bucket_attrs);
5978 attrs.erase(RGW_ATTR_CORS);
5979 op_ret = s->bucket->merge_and_store_attrs(this, attrs, s->yield);
5980 if (op_ret < 0) {
5981 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "RGWLC::RGWDeleteCORS() failed to set attrs on bucket=" << s->bucket->get_name()
5982 << " returned err=" << op_ret << dendl;
5983 }
5984 return op_ret;
5985 });
5986}
5987
5988void RGWOptionsCORS::get_response_params(string& hdrs, string& exp_hdrs, unsigned *max_age) {
5989 get_cors_response_headers(this, rule, req_hdrs, hdrs, exp_hdrs, max_age);
5990}
5991
5992int RGWOptionsCORS::validate_cors_request(RGWCORSConfiguration *cc) {
5993 rule = cc->host_name_rule(origin);
5994 if (!rule) {
5995 ldpp_dout(this, 10) << "There is no cors rule present for " << origin << dendl;
5996 return -ENOENT;
5997 }
5998
5999 if (!validate_cors_rule_method(this, rule, req_meth)) {
6000 return -ENOENT;
6001 }
6002
6003 if (!validate_cors_rule_header(this, rule, req_hdrs)) {
6004 return -ENOENT;
6005 }
6006
6007 return 0;
6008}
6009
6010void RGWOptionsCORS::execute(optional_yield y)
6011{
6012 op_ret = read_bucket_cors();
6013 if (op_ret < 0)
6014 return;
6015
6016 origin = s->info.env->get("HTTP_ORIGIN");
6017 if (!origin) {
6018 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "Missing mandatory Origin header" << dendl;
6019 op_ret = -EINVAL;
6020 return;
6021 }
6022 req_meth = s->info.env->get("HTTP_ACCESS_CONTROL_REQUEST_METHOD");
6023 if (!req_meth) {
6024 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "Missing mandatory Access-control-request-method header" << dendl;
6025 op_ret = -EINVAL;
6026 return;
6027 }
6028 if (!cors_exist) {
6029 ldpp_dout(this, 2) << "No CORS configuration set yet for this bucket" << dendl;
6030 op_ret = -ENOENT;
6031 return;
6032 }
6033 req_hdrs = s->info.env->get("HTTP_ACCESS_CONTROL_REQUEST_HEADERS");
6034 op_ret = validate_cors_request(&bucket_cors);
6035 if (!rule) {
6036 origin = req_meth = NULL;
6037 return;
6038 }
6039 return;
6040}

6098
6099int RGWInitMultipart::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
6100{
6101 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s);
6102 if (has_s3_existing_tag || has_s3_resource_tag)
6103 rgw_iam_add_objtags(this, s, has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag);
6104
6105 if (s->iam_policy || ! s->iam_user_policies.empty() || !s->session_policies.empty()) {
6106 auto identity_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->iam_user_policies, s->env,
6107 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
6108 s->object->get_obj());
6109 if (identity_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
6110 return -EACCES;
6111 }
6112
6113 rgw::IAM::Effect e = Effect::Pass;
6114 rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal princ_type = rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other;
6115 ARN obj_arn(s->object->get_obj());
6116 if (s->iam_policy) {
6117 e = s->iam_policy->eval(s->env, *s->auth.identity,
6118 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
6119 obj_arn,
6120 princ_type);
6121 }
6122 if (e == Effect::Deny) {
6123 return -EACCES;
6124 }
6125
6126 if (!s->session_policies.empty()) {
6127 auto session_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->session_policies, s->env,
6128 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
6129 s->object->get_obj());
6130 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
6131 return -EACCES;
6132 }
6133 if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Role) {
6134 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus intersection of session policy and bucket policy
6135 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) ||
6136 (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && e == Effect::Allow)) {
6137 return 0;
6138 }
6139 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Session) {
6140 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus bucket policy
6141 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) || e == Effect::Allow) {
6142 return 0;
6143 }
6144 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other) {// there was no match in the bucket policy
6145 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) {
6146 return 0;
6147 }
6148 }
6149 return -EACCES;
6150 }
6151 if (e == Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) {
6152 return 0;
6153 }
6154 }
6155
6156 if (!verify_bucket_permission_no_policy(this, s, RGW_PERM_WRITE)) {
6157 return -EACCES;
6158 }
6159
6160 return 0;
6161}
6162
6163void RGWInitMultipart::pre_exec()
6164{
6165 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
6166}
6167
6168void RGWInitMultipart::execute(optional_yield y)
6169{
6170 bufferlist aclbl, tracebl;
6171 rgw::sal::Attrs attrs;
6172
6173 if (get_params(y) < 0)
6174 return;
6175
6176 if (rgw::sal::Object::empty(s->object.get()))
6177 return;
6178
6179 if (multipart_trace) {
6180 tracing::encode(multipart_trace->GetContext(), tracebl);
6181 attrs[RGW_ATTR_TRACE] = tracebl;
6182 }
6183
6184 policy.encode(aclbl);
6185 attrs[RGW_ATTR_ACL] = aclbl;
6186
6187 populate_with_generic_attrs(s, attrs);
6188
6189 /* select encryption mode */
6190 op_ret = prepare_encryption(attrs);
6191 if (op_ret != 0)
6192 return;
6193
6194 op_ret = rgw_get_request_metadata(this, s->cct, s->info, attrs);
6195 if (op_ret < 0) {
6196 return;
6197 }
6198
6199 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::MultipartUpload> upload;
6200 upload = s->bucket->get_multipart_upload(s->object->get_name(),
6201 upload_id);
6202 op_ret = upload->init(this, s->yield, s->obj_ctx, s->owner, s->dest_placement, attrs);
6203
6204 if (op_ret == 0) {
6205 upload_id = upload->get_upload_id();
6206 }
6207 s->trace->SetAttribute(tracing::rgw::UPLOAD_ID, upload_id);
6208 multipart_trace->UpdateName(tracing::rgw::MULTIPART + upload_id);
6209
6210}
6211
6212int RGWCompleteMultipart::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
6213{
6214 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s);
6215 if (has_s3_existing_tag || has_s3_resource_tag)
6216 rgw_iam_add_objtags(this, s, has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag);
6217
6218 if (s->iam_policy || ! s->iam_user_policies.empty() || ! s->session_policies.empty()) {
6219 auto identity_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->iam_user_policies, s->env,
6220 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
6221 s->object->get_obj());
6222 if (identity_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
6223 return -EACCES;
6224 }
6225
6226 rgw::IAM::Effect e = Effect::Pass;
6227 rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal princ_type = rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other;
6228 rgw::ARN obj_arn(s->object->get_obj());
6229 if (s->iam_policy) {
6230 e = s->iam_policy->eval(s->env, *s->auth.identity,
6231 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
6232 obj_arn,
6233 princ_type);
6234 }
6235 if (e == Effect::Deny) {
6236 return -EACCES;
6237 }
6238
6239 if (!s->session_policies.empty()) {
6240 auto session_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->session_policies, s->env,
6241 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
6242 s->object->get_obj());
6243 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
6244 return -EACCES;
6245 }
6246 if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Role) {
6247 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus intersection of session policy and bucket policy
6248 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) ||
6249 (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && e == Effect::Allow)) {
6250 return 0;
6251 }
6252 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Session) {
6253 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus bucket policy
6254 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) || e == Effect::Allow) {
6255 return 0;
6256 }
6257 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other) {// there was no match in the bucket policy
6258 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) {
6259 return 0;
6260 }
6261 }
6262 return -EACCES;
6263 }
6264 if (e == Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) {
6265 return 0;
6266 }
6267 }
6268
6269 if (!verify_bucket_permission_no_policy(this, s, RGW_PERM_WRITE)) {
6270 return -EACCES;
6271 }
6272
6273 return 0;
6274}

6277{
6278 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);

6280
6281void RGWCompleteMultipart::execute(optional_yield y)
6282{
6283 RGWMultiCompleteUpload *parts;
6284 RGWMultiXMLParser parser;
6285 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::MultipartUpload> upload;
6286 off_t ofs = 0;
6287 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Object> meta_obj;
6288 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Object> target_obj;
6289 uint64_t olh_epoch = 0;
6290
6291 op_ret = get_params(y);
6292 if (op_ret < 0)
6293 return;
6294 op_ret = get_system_versioning_params(s, &olh_epoch, &version_id);
6295 if (op_ret < 0) {
6296 return;
6297 }
6298
6299 if (!data.length()) {
6300 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;
6301 return;
6302 }
6303
6304 if (!parser.init()) {
6305 op_ret = -EIO;
6306 return;
6307 }
6308
6309 if (!parser.parse(data.c_str(), data.length(), 1)) {
6310 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;
6311 return;
6312 }
6313
6314 parts = static_cast<RGWMultiCompleteUpload *>(parser.find_first("CompleteMultipartUpload"));
6315 if (!parts || parts->parts.empty()) {
6316 // CompletedMultipartUpload is incorrect but some versions of some libraries use it, see PR #41700
6317 parts = static_cast<RGWMultiCompleteUpload *>(parser.find_first("CompletedMultipartUpload"));
6318 }
6319
6320 if (!parts || parts->parts.empty()) {
6321 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;
6322 return;
6323 }
6324
6325
6326 if ((int)parts->parts.size() >
6327 s->cct->_conf->rgw_multipart_part_upload_limit) {
6328 op_ret = -ERANGE;
6329 return;
6330 }
6331
6332 upload = s->bucket->get_multipart_upload(s->object->get_name(), upload_id);
6333
6334 RGWCompressionInfo cs_info;
6335 bool compressed = false;
6336 uint64_t accounted_size = 0;
6337
6338 list<rgw_obj_index_key> remove_objs; /* objects to be removed from index listing */
6339
6340 meta_obj = upload->get_meta_obj();
6341 meta_obj->set_in_extra_data(true);
6342 meta_obj->set_hash_source(s->object->get_name());
6343
6344 /*take a cls lock on meta_obj to prevent racing completions (or retries)
6345 from deleting the parts*/
6346 int max_lock_secs_mp =
6347 s->cct->_conf.get_val<int64_t>("rgw_mp_lock_max_time");
6348 utime_t dur(max_lock_secs_mp, 0);
6349
6350 serializer = meta_obj->get_serializer(this, "RGWCompleteMultipart");
6351 op_ret = serializer->try_lock(this, dur, y);
6352 if (op_ret < 0) {
6353 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "failed to acquire lock" << dendl;
6354 if (op_ret == -ENOENT && check_previously_completed(parts)) {
6355 ldpp_dout(this, 1) << "NOTICE: This multipart completion is already completed" << dendl;
6356 op_ret = 0;
6357 return;
6358 }
6359 op_ret = -ERR_INTERNAL_ERROR;
6360 s->err.message = "This multipart completion is already in progress";
6361 return;
6362 }
6363
6364 op_ret = meta_obj->get_obj_attrs(s->obj_ctx, s->yield, this);
6365 if (op_ret < 0) {
6366 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: failed to get obj attrs, obj=" << meta_obj
6367 << " ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
6368 return;
6369 }
6370 s->trace->SetAttribute(tracing::rgw::UPLOAD_ID, upload_id);
6371 jspan_context trace_ctx(false, false);
6372 extract_span_context(meta_obj->get_attrs(), trace_ctx);
6373 multipart_trace = tracing::rgw::tracer.add_span(name(), trace_ctx);
6374
6375
6376 // make reservation for notification if needed
6377 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Notification> res
6378 = store->get_notification(meta_obj.get(), nullptr, s, rgw::notify::ObjectCreatedCompleteMultipartUpload, &s->object->get_name());
6379 op_ret = res->publish_reserve(this);
6380 if (op_ret < 0) {
6381 return;
6382 }
6383
6384 target_obj = s->bucket->get_object(rgw_obj_key(s->object->get_name()));
6385 if (s->bucket->versioning_enabled()) {
6386 if (!version_id.empty()) {
6387 target_obj->set_instance(version_id);
6388 } else {
6389 target_obj->gen_rand_obj_instance_name();
6390 version_id = target_obj->get_instance();
6391 }
6392 }
6393 target_obj->set_attrs(meta_obj->get_attrs());
6394
6395 op_ret = upload->complete(this, y, s->cct, parts->parts, remove_objs, accounted_size, compressed, cs_info, ofs, s->req_id, s->owner, olh_epoch, target_obj.get(), s->obj_ctx);
6396 if (op_ret < 0) {
6397 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: upload complete failed ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
6398 return;
6399 }
6400
6401 // remove the upload meta object ; the meta object is not versioned
6402 // when the bucket is, as that would add an unneeded delete marker
6403 int r = meta_obj->delete_object(this, s->obj_ctx, y, true /* prevent versioning */);
6404 if (r >= 0) {
6405 /* serializer's exclusive lock is released */
6406 serializer->clear_locked();
6407 } else {
6408 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "WARNING: failed to remove object " << meta_obj << dendl;
6409 }
6410
6411 // send request to notification manager
6412 int ret = res->publish_commit(this, ofs, target_obj->get_mtime(), etag, target_obj->get_instance());
6413 if (ret < 0) {
6414 ldpp_dout(this, 1) << "ERROR: publishing notification failed, with error: " << ret << dendl;
6415 // too late to rollback operation, hence op_ret is not set here
6416 }
6417} // RGWCompleteMultipart::execute
6418
6419bool RGWCompleteMultipart::check_previously_completed(const RGWMultiCompleteUpload* parts)
6420{
6421 // re-calculate the etag from the parts and compare to the existing object
6422 int ret = s->object->get_obj_attrs(s->obj_ctx, s->yield, this);
6423 if (ret < 0) {
6424 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << __func__ << "() ERROR: get_obj_attrs() returned ret=" << ret << dendl;
6425 return false;
6426 }
6427 rgw::sal::Attrs sattrs = s->object->get_attrs();
6428 string oetag = sattrs[RGW_ATTR_ETAG].to_str();
6429
6430 MD5 hash;
6431 // Allow use of MD5 digest in FIPS mode for non-cryptographic purposes
6432 hash.SetFlags(EVP_MD_CTX_FLAG_NON_FIPS_ALLOW);
6433 for (const auto& [index, part] : parts->parts) {
6434 std::string partetag = rgw_string_unquote(part);
6435 char petag[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE];
6436 hex_to_buf(partetag.c_str(), petag, CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE);
6437 hash.Update((const unsigned char *)petag, sizeof(petag));
6438 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << __func__ << "() re-calculating multipart etag: part: "
6439 << index << ", etag: " << partetag << dendl;
6440 }
6441
6442 unsigned char final_etag[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE];
6443 char final_etag_str[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE * 2 + 16];
6444 hash.Final(final_etag);
6445 buf_to_hex(final_etag, CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE, final_etag_str);
6446 snprintf(&final_etag_str[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE * 2], sizeof(final_etag_str) - CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE * 2,
6447 "-%lld", (long long)parts->parts.size());
6448
6449 if (oetag.compare(final_etag_str) != 0) {
6450 ldpp_dout(this, 1) << __func__ << "() NOTICE: etag mismatch: object etag:"
6451 << oetag << ", re-calculated etag:" << final_etag_str << dendl;
6452 return false;
6453 }
6454 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << __func__ << "() object etag and re-calculated etag match, etag: " << oetag << dendl;
6455 return true;
6456}
6457
6458void RGWCompleteMultipart::complete()
6459{
6460 /* release exclusive lock iff not already */
6461 if (unlikely(serializer && serializer->locked)) {
6462 int r = serializer->unlock();
6463 if (r < 0) {
6464 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "WARNING: failed to unlock " << serializer->oid << dendl;
6465 }
6466 }
6467 send_response();
6468}

6470int RGWAbortMultipart::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
6471{
6472 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s);
6473 if (has_s3_existing_tag || has_s3_resource_tag)
6474 rgw_iam_add_objtags(this, s, has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag);
6475
6476 if (s->iam_policy || ! s->iam_user_policies.empty() || !s->session_policies.empty()) {
6477 auto identity_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->iam_user_policies, s->env,
6478 rgw::IAM::s3AbortMultipartUpload,
6479 s->object->get_obj());
6480 if (identity_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
6481 return -EACCES;
6482 }
6483
6484 rgw::IAM::Effect e = Effect::Pass;
6485 rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal princ_type = rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other;
6486 ARN obj_arn(s->object->get_obj());
6487 if (s->iam_policy) {
6488 e = s->iam_policy->eval(s->env, *s->auth.identity,
6489 rgw::IAM::s3AbortMultipartUpload,
6490 obj_arn, princ_type);
6491 }
6492
6493 if (e == Effect::Deny) {
6494 return -EACCES;
6495 }
6496
6497 if (!s->session_policies.empty()) {
6498 auto session_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->session_policies, s->env,
6499 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject,
6500 s->object->get_obj());
6501 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
6502 return -EACCES;
6503 }
6504 if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Role) {
6505 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus intersection of session policy and bucket policy
6506 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) ||
6507 (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && e == Effect::Allow)) {
6508 return 0;
6509 }
6510 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Session) {
6511 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus bucket policy
6512 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) || e == Effect::Allow) {
6513 return 0;
6514 }
6515 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other) {// there was no match in the bucket policy
6516 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) {
6517 return 0;
6518 }
6519 }
6520 return -EACCES;
6521 }
6522 if (e == Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) {
6523 return 0;
6524 }
6525 }
6526
6527 if (!verify_bucket_permission_no_policy(this, s, RGW_PERM_WRITE)) {
6528 return -EACCES;
6529 }
6530
6531 return 0;
6532}

6539void RGWAbortMultipart::execute(optional_yield y)
6540{
6541 op_ret = -EINVAL;
6542 string upload_id;
6543 upload_id = s->info.args.get("uploadId");
6544 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Object> meta_obj;
6545 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::MultipartUpload> upload;
6546
6547 if (upload_id.empty() || rgw::sal::Object::empty(s->object.get()))
6548 return;
6549
6550 upload = s->bucket->get_multipart_upload(s->object->get_name(), upload_id);
6551 RGWObjectCtx *obj_ctx = static_cast<RGWObjectCtx *>(s->obj_ctx);
6552
6553 jspan_context trace_ctx(false, false);
6554 if (tracing::rgw::tracer.is_enabled()) {
6555 // read meta object attributes for trace info
6556 meta_obj = upload->get_meta_obj();
6557 meta_obj->set_in_extra_data(true);
6558 meta_obj->get_obj_attrs(obj_ctx, s->yield, this);
6559 extract_span_context(meta_obj->get_attrs(), trace_ctx);
6560 }
6561 multipart_trace = tracing::rgw::tracer.add_span(name(), trace_ctx);
6562
6563 op_ret = upload->abort(this, s->cct, obj_ctx);
6564}

6582
6583void RGWListMultipart::execute(optional_yield y)
6584{
6585 op_ret = get_params(y);
6586 if (op_ret < 0)
6587 return;
6588
6589 upload = s->bucket->get_multipart_upload(s->object->get_name(), upload_id);
6590
6591 rgw::sal::Attrs attrs;
6592 op_ret = upload->get_info(this, s->yield, s->obj_ctx, &placement, &attrs);
6593 /* decode policy */
6594 map<string, bufferlist>::iterator iter = attrs.find(RGW_ATTR_ACL);
6595 if (iter != attrs.end()) {
6596 auto bliter = iter->second.cbegin();
6597 try {
6598 policy.decode(bliter);
6599 } catch (buffer::error& err) {
6600 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: could not decode policy, caught buffer::error" << dendl;
6601 op_ret = -EIO;
6602 }
6603 }
6604 if (op_ret < 0)
6605 return;
6606
6607 op_ret = upload->list_parts(this, s->cct, max_parts, marker, NULL, &truncated);
6608}

6613 if (has_s3_resource_tag)

6615

6617 s,
6618 rgw::IAM::s3ListBucketMultipartUploads))

6628
6629void RGWListBucketMultiparts::execute(optional_yield y)
6630{
6631 op_ret = get_params(y);
6632 if (op_ret < 0)
6633 return;
6634
6635 if (s->prot_flags & RGW_REST_SWIFT) {
6636 string path_args;
6637 path_args = s->info.args.get("path");
6638 if (!path_args.empty()) {
6639 if (!delimiter.empty() || !prefix.empty()) {
6640 op_ret = -EINVAL;
6641 return;
6642 }
6643 prefix = path_args;
6644 delimiter="/";
6645 }
6646 }
6647
6648 op_ret = s->bucket->list_multiparts(this, prefix, marker_meta,
6649 delimiter, max_uploads, uploads,
6650 &common_prefixes, &is_truncated);
6651 if (op_ret < 0) {
6652 return;
6653 }
6654
6655 if (!uploads.empty()) {
6656 next_marker_key = uploads.back()->get_key();
6657 next_marker_upload_id = uploads.back()->get_upload_id();
6658 }
6659}

6669 }

6671
6672int RGWDeleteMultiObj::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
6673{
6674 int op_ret = get_params(y);
6675 if (op_ret) {
6676 return op_ret;
6677 }
6678
6679 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s);
6680 if (has_s3_existing_tag || has_s3_resource_tag)
6681 rgw_iam_add_objtags(this, s, has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag);
6682
6683 if (s->iam_policy || ! s->iam_user_policies.empty() || ! s->session_policies.empty()) {
6684 if (s->bucket->get_info().obj_lock_enabled() && bypass_governance_mode) {
6685 ARN bucket_arn(s->bucket->get_key());
6686 auto r = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->iam_user_policies, s->env,
6687 rgw::IAM::s3BypassGovernanceRetention, ARN(s->bucket->get_key()));
6688 if (r == Effect::Deny) {
6689 bypass_perm = false;
6690 } else if (r == Effect::Pass && s->iam_policy) {
6691 r = s->iam_policy->eval(s->env, *s->auth.identity, rgw::IAM::s3BypassGovernanceRetention,
6692 bucket_arn);
6693 if (r == Effect::Deny) {
6694 bypass_perm = false;
6695 }
6696 } else if (r == Effect::Pass && !s->session_policies.empty()) {
6697 r = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->session_policies, s->env,
6698 rgw::IAM::s3BypassGovernanceRetention, ARN(s->bucket->get_key()));
6699 if (r == Effect::Deny) {
6700 bypass_perm = false;
6701 }
6702 }
6703 }
6704
6705 bool not_versioned = rgw::sal::Object::empty(s->object.get()) || s->object->get_instance().empty();
6706
6707 auto identity_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->iam_user_policies, s->env,
6708 not_versioned ?
6709 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObject :
6710 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObjectVersion,
6711 ARN(s->bucket->get_key()));
6712 if (identity_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
6713 return -EACCES;
6714 }
6715
6716 rgw::IAM::Effect r = Effect::Pass;
6717 rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal princ_type = rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other;
6718 rgw::ARN bucket_arn(s->bucket->get_key());
6719 if (s->iam_policy) {
6720 r = s->iam_policy->eval(s->env, *s->auth.identity,
6721 not_versioned ?
6722 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObject :
6723 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObjectVersion,
6724 bucket_arn,
6725 princ_type);
6726 }
6727 if (r == Effect::Deny)
6728 return -EACCES;
6729
6730 if (!s->session_policies.empty()) {
6731 auto session_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->session_policies, s->env,
6732 not_versioned ?
6733 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObject :
6734 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObjectVersion,
6735 ARN(s->bucket->get_key()));
6736 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
6737 return -EACCES;
6738 }
6739 if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Role) {
6740 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus intersection of session policy and bucket policy
6741 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) ||
6742 (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && r == Effect::Allow)) {
6743 return 0;
6744 }
6745 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Session) {
6746 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus bucket policy
6747 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) || r == Effect::Allow) {
6748 return 0;
6749 }
6750 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other) {// there was no match in the bucket policy
6751 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) {
6752 return 0;
6753 }
6754 }
6755 return -EACCES;
6756 }
6757 if (r == Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow)
6758 return 0;
6759 }
6760
6761 acl_allowed = verify_bucket_permission_no_policy(this, s, RGW_PERM_WRITE);
6762 if (!acl_allowed)
6763 return -EACCES;
6764
6765 return 0;
6766}
6767
6768void RGWDeleteMultiObj::pre_exec()
6769{
6770 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
6771}
6772
6773void RGWDeleteMultiObj::write_ops_log_entry(rgw_log_entry& entry) const {
6774 int num_err = 0;
6775 int num_ok = 0;
6776 for (auto iter = ops_log_entries.begin();
6777 iter != ops_log_entries.end();
6778 ++iter) {
6779 if (iter->error) {
6780 num_err++;
6781 } else {
6782 num_ok++;
6783 }
6784 }
6785 entry.delete_multi_obj_meta.num_err = num_err;
6786 entry.delete_multi_obj_meta.num_ok = num_ok;
6787 entry.delete_multi_obj_meta.objects = std::move(ops_log_entries);
6788}
6789
6790void RGWDeleteMultiObj::execute(optional_yield y)
6791{
6792 RGWMultiDelDelete *multi_delete;
6793 vector<rgw_obj_key>::iterator iter;
6794 RGWMultiDelXMLParser parser;
6795 RGWObjectCtx *obj_ctx = static_cast<RGWObjectCtx *>(s->obj_ctx);
6796 char* buf;
6797
6798 buf = data.c_str();
6799 if (!buf) {
6800 op_ret = -EINVAL;
6801 goto error;
6802 }
6803
6804 if (!parser.init()) {
6805 op_ret = -EINVAL;
6806 goto error;
6807 }
6808
6809 if (!parser.parse(buf, data.length(), 1)) {
6810 op_ret = -EINVAL;
6811 goto error;
6812 }
6813
6814 multi_delete = static_cast<RGWMultiDelDelete *>(parser.find_first("Delete"));
6815 if (!multi_delete) {
6816 op_ret = -EINVAL;
6817 goto error;
6818 } else {
6819#define DELETE_MULTI_OBJ_MAX_NUM 1000
6820 int max_num = s->cct->_conf->rgw_delete_multi_obj_max_num;
6821 if (max_num < 0) {
6822 max_num = DELETE_MULTI_OBJ_MAX_NUM;
6823 }
6824 int multi_delete_object_num = multi_delete->objects.size();
6825 if (multi_delete_object_num > max_num) {
6826 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;
6827 goto error;
6828 }
6829 }
6830
6831 if (multi_delete->is_quiet())
6832 quiet = true;
6833
6834 if (s->bucket->get_info().mfa_enabled()) {
6835 bool has_versioned = false;
6836 for (auto i : multi_delete->objects) {
6837 if (!i.instance.empty()) {
6838 has_versioned = true;
6839 break;
6840 }
6841 }
6842 if (has_versioned && !s->mfa_verified) {
6843 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << "NOTICE: multi-object delete request with a versioned object, mfa auth not provided" << dendl;
6844 op_ret = -ERR_MFA_REQUIRED;
6845 goto error;
6846 }
6847 }
6848
6849 begin_response();
6850 if (multi_delete->objects.empty()) {
6851 goto done;
6852 }
6853
6854 for (iter = multi_delete->objects.begin();
6855 iter != multi_delete->objects.end();
6856 ++iter) {
6857 std::string version_id;
6858 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Object> obj = bucket->get_object(*iter);
6859 if (s->iam_policy || ! s->iam_user_policies.empty() || !s->session_policies.empty()) {
6860 auto identity_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->iam_user_policies, s->env,
6861 iter->instance.empty() ?
6862 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObject :
6863 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObjectVersion,
6864 ARN(obj->get_obj()));
6865 if (identity_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
6866 send_partial_response(*iter, false, "", -EACCES);
6867 continue;
6868 }
6869
6870 rgw::IAM::Effect e = Effect::Pass;
6871 rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal princ_type = rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other;
6872 if (s->iam_policy) {
6873 ARN obj_arn(obj->get_obj());
6874 e = s->iam_policy->eval(s->env,
6875 *s->auth.identity,
6876 iter->instance.empty() ?
6877 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObject :
6878 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObjectVersion,
6879 obj_arn,
6880 princ_type);
6881 }
6882 if (e == Effect::Deny) {
6883 send_partial_response(*iter, false, "", -EACCES);
6884 continue;
6885 }
6886
6887 if (!s->session_policies.empty()) {
6888 auto session_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->session_policies, s->env,
6889 iter->instance.empty() ?
6890 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObject :
6891 rgw::IAM::s3DeleteObjectVersion,
6892 ARN(obj->get_obj()));
6893 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
6894 send_partial_response(*iter, false, "", -EACCES);
6895 continue;
6896 }
6897 if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Role) {
6898 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus intersection of session policy and bucket policy
6899 if ((session_policy_res != Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res != Effect::Allow) &&
6900 (session_policy_res != Effect::Allow || e != Effect::Allow)) {
6901 send_partial_response(*iter, false, "", -EACCES);
6902 continue;
6903 }
6904 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Session) {
6905 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus bucket policy
6906 if ((session_policy_res != Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res != Effect::Allow) && e != Effect::Allow) {
6907 send_partial_response(*iter, false, "", -EACCES);
6908 continue;
6909 }
6910 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other) {// there was no match in the bucket policy
6911 if (session_policy_res != Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res != Effect::Allow) {
6912 send_partial_response(*iter, false, "", -EACCES);
6913 continue;
6914 }
6915 }
6916 send_partial_response(*iter, false, "", -EACCES);
6917 continue;
6918 }
6919
6920 if ((identity_policy_res == Effect::Pass && e == Effect::Pass && !acl_allowed)) {
6921 send_partial_response(*iter, false, "", -EACCES);
6922 continue;
6923 }
6924 }
6925
6926 uint64_t obj_size = 0;
6927 std::string etag;
6928
6929 if (!rgw::sal::Object::empty(obj.get())) {
6930 RGWObjState* astate = nullptr;
6931 bool check_obj_lock = obj->have_instance() && bucket->get_info().obj_lock_enabled();
6932 const auto ret = obj->get_obj_state(this, obj_ctx, &astate, s->yield, true);
6933
6934 if (ret < 0) {
6935 if (ret == -ENOENT) {
6936 // object maybe delete_marker, skip check_obj_lock
6937 check_obj_lock = false;
6938 } else {
6939 // Something went wrong.
6940 send_partial_response(*iter, false, "", ret);
6941 continue;
6942 }
6943 } else {
6944 obj_size = astate->size;
6945 etag = astate->attrset[RGW_ATTR_ETAG].to_str();
6946 }
6947
6948 if (check_obj_lock) {
6949 ceph_assert(astate);
6950 int object_lock_response = verify_object_lock(this, astate->attrset, bypass_perm, bypass_governance_mode);
6951 if (object_lock_response != 0) {
6952 send_partial_response(*iter, false, "", object_lock_response);
6953 continue;
6954 }
6955 }
6956 }
6957
6958 // make reservation for notification if needed
6959 const auto versioned_object = s->bucket->versioning_enabled();
6960 const auto event_type = versioned_object && obj->get_instance().empty() ?
6961 rgw::notify::ObjectRemovedDeleteMarkerCreated :
6962 rgw::notify::ObjectRemovedDelete;
6963 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Notification> res
6964 = store->get_notification(obj.get(), s->src_object.get(), s, event_type);
6965 op_ret = res->publish_reserve(this);
6966 if (op_ret < 0) {
6967 send_partial_response(*iter, false, "", op_ret);
6968 continue;
6969 }
6970
6971 obj->set_atomic(obj_ctx);
6972
6973 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Object::DeleteOp> del_op = obj->get_delete_op(obj_ctx);
6974 del_op->params.versioning_status = obj->get_bucket()->get_info().versioning_status();
6975 del_op->params.obj_owner = s->owner;
6976 del_op->params.bucket_owner = s->bucket_owner;
6977 del_op->params.marker_version_id = version_id;
6978
6979 op_ret = del_op->delete_obj(this, y);
6980 if (op_ret == -ENOENT) {
6981 op_ret = 0;
6982 }
6983
6984 send_partial_response(*iter, obj->get_delete_marker(), del_op->result.version_id, op_ret);
6985
6986 // send request to notification manager
6987 int ret = res->publish_commit(this, obj_size, ceph::real_clock::now(), etag, version_id);
6988 if (ret < 0) {
6989 ldpp_dout(this, 1) << "ERROR: publishing notification failed, with error: " << ret << dendl;
6990 // too late to rollback operation, hence op_ret is not set here
6991 }
6992 }
6993
6994 /* set the return code to zero, errors at this point will be
6995 dumped to the response */
6996 op_ret = 0;
6997
6998done:
6999 // will likely segfault if begin_response() has not been called
7000 end_response();
7001 return;
7002
7003error:
7004 send_status();
7005 return;
7006
7007}
7008
7009bool RGWBulkDelete::Deleter::verify_permission(RGWBucketInfo& binfo,
7010 map<string, bufferlist>& battrs,
7011 ACLOwner& bucket_owner /* out */,
7012 optional_yield y)
7013{
7014 RGWAccessControlPolicy bacl(store->ctx());
7015 int ret = read_bucket_policy(dpp, store, s, binfo, battrs, &bacl, binfo.bucket, y);
7016 if (ret < 0) {
7017 return false;
7018 }
7019
7020 auto policy = get_iam_policy_from_attr(s->cct, battrs, binfo.bucket.tenant);
7021
7022 bucket_owner = bacl.get_owner();
7023
7024 /* We can use global user_acl because each BulkDelete request is allowed
7025 * to work on entities from a single account only. */
7026 return verify_bucket_permission(dpp, s, binfo.bucket, s->user_acl.get(),
7027 &bacl, policy, s->iam_user_policies, s->session_policies, rgw::IAM::s3DeleteBucket);
7028}
7029
7030bool RGWBulkDelete::Deleter::delete_single(const acct_path_t& path, optional_yield y)
7031{
7032 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Bucket> bucket;
7033 ACLOwner bowner;
7034 RGWObjVersionTracker ot;
7035
7036 int ret = store->get_bucket(dpp, s->user.get(), s->user->get_tenant(), path.bucket_name, &bucket, y);
7037 if (ret < 0) {
7038 goto binfo_fail;
7039 }
7040
7041 ret = bucket->load_bucket(dpp, s->yield);
7042 if (ret < 0) {
7043 goto binfo_fail;
7044 }
7045
7046 if (!verify_permission(bucket->get_info(), bucket->get_attrs(), bowner, y)) {
7047 ret = -EACCES;
7048 goto auth_fail;
7049 }
7050
7051 if (!path.obj_key.empty()) {
7052 ACLOwner bucket_owner;
7053
7054 bucket_owner.set_id(bucket->get_info().owner);
7055 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Object> obj = bucket->get_object(path.obj_key);
7056 obj->set_atomic(s->obj_ctx);
7057
7058 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Object::DeleteOp> del_op = obj->get_delete_op(s->obj_ctx);
7059 del_op->params.versioning_status = obj->get_bucket()->get_info().versioning_status();
7060 del_op->params.obj_owner = bowner;
7061 del_op->params.bucket_owner = bucket_owner;
7062
7063 ret = del_op->delete_obj(dpp, y);
7064 if (ret < 0) {
7065 goto delop_fail;
7066 }
7067 } else {
7068 ret = bucket->remove_bucket(dpp, false, true, &s->info, s->yield);
7069 if (ret < 0) {
7070 goto delop_fail;
7071 }
7072 }
7073
7074 num_deleted++;
7075 return true;
7076
7077binfo_fail:
7078 if (-ENOENT == ret) {
7079 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "cannot find bucket = " << path.bucket_name << dendl;
7080 num_unfound++;
7081 } else {
7082 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "cannot get bucket info, ret = " << ret << dendl;
7083
7084 fail_desc_t failed_item = {
7085 .err = ret,
7086 .path = path
7087 };
7088 failures.push_back(failed_item);
7089 }
7090 return false;
7091
7092auth_fail:
7093 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "wrong auth for " << path << dendl;
7094 {
7095 fail_desc_t failed_item = {
7096 .err = ret,
7097 .path = path
7098 };
7099 failures.push_back(failed_item);
7100 }
7101 return false;
7102
7103delop_fail:
7104 if (-ENOENT == ret) {
7105 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "cannot find entry " << path << dendl;
7106 num_unfound++;
7107 } else {
7108 fail_desc_t failed_item = {
7109 .err = ret,
7110 .path = path
7111 };
7112 failures.push_back(failed_item);
7113 }
7114 return false;
7115}
7116
7117bool RGWBulkDelete::Deleter::delete_chunk(const std::list<acct_path_t>& paths, optional_yield y)
7118{
7119 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "in delete_chunk" << dendl;
7120 for (auto path : paths) {
7121 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "bulk deleting path: " << path << dendl;
7122 delete_single(path, y);
7123 }
7124
7125 return true;
7126}
7127
7128int RGWBulkDelete::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
7129{
7130 return 0;
7131}
7132
7133void RGWBulkDelete::pre_exec()
7134{
7135 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
7136}
7137
7138void RGWBulkDelete::execute(optional_yield y)
7139{
7140 deleter = std::unique_ptr<Deleter>(new Deleter(this, store, s));
7141
7142 bool is_truncated = false;
7143 do {
7144 list<RGWBulkDelete::acct_path_t> items;
7145
7146 int ret = get_data(items, &is_truncated);
7147 if (ret < 0) {
7148 return;
7149 }
7150
7151 ret = deleter->delete_chunk(items, y);
7152 } while (!op_ret && is_truncated);
7153
7154 return;
7155}

7157
7158constexpr std::array<int, 2> RGWBulkUploadOp::terminal_errors;
7159
7160int RGWBulkUploadOp::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
7161{
7162 if (s->auth.identity->is_anonymous()) {
7163 return -EACCES;
7164 }
7165
7166 if (! verify_user_permission_no_policy(this, s, RGW_PERM_WRITE)) {
7167 return -EACCES;
7168 }
7169
7170 if (s->user->get_tenant() != s->bucket_tenant) {
7171 ldpp_dout(this, 10) << "user cannot create a bucket in a different tenant"
7172 << " (user_id.tenant=" << s->user->get_tenant()
7173 << " requested=" << s->bucket_tenant << ")" << dendl;
7174 return -EACCES;
7175 }
7176
7177 if (s->user->get_max_buckets() < 0) {
7178 return -EPERM;
7179 }
7180
7181 return 0;
7182}
