7185{
7186 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
7187}
7188
7189boost::optional<std::pair<std::string, rgw_obj_key>>
7190RGWBulkUploadOp::parse_path(const std::string_view& path)
7191{
7192 /* We need to skip all slashes at the beginning in order to preserve
7193 * compliance with Swift. */
7194 const size_t start_pos = path.find_first_not_of('/');
7195
7196 if (std::string_view::npos != start_pos) {
7197 /* Seperator is the first slash after the leading ones. */
7198 const size_t sep_pos = path.substr(start_pos).find('/');
7199
7200 if (std::string_view::npos != sep_pos) {
7201 const auto bucket_name = path.substr(start_pos, sep_pos - start_pos);
7202 const auto obj_name = path.substr(sep_pos + 1);
7203
7204 return std::make_pair(std::string(bucket_name),
7205 rgw_obj_key(std::string(obj_name)));
7206 } else {
7207 /* It's guaranteed here that bucket name is at least one character
7208 * long and is different than slash. */
7209 return std::make_pair(std::string(path.substr(start_pos)),
7210 rgw_obj_key());
7211 }
7212 }
7213
7214 return none;
7215}
7216
7217std::pair<std::string, std::string>
7218RGWBulkUploadOp::handle_upload_path(struct req_state *s)
7219{
7220 std::string bucket_path, file_prefix;
7221 if (! s->init_state.url_bucket.empty()) {
7222 file_prefix = bucket_path = s->init_state.url_bucket + "/";
7223 if (!rgw::sal::Object::empty(s->object.get())) {
7224 const std::string& object_name = s->object->get_name();
7225
7226 /* As rgw_obj_key::empty() already verified emptiness of s->object->get_name(),
7227 * we can safely examine its last element. */
7228 if (object_name.back() == '/') {
7229 file_prefix.append(object_name);
7230 } else {
7231 file_prefix.append(object_name).append("/");
7232 }
7233 }
7234 }
7235 return std::make_pair(bucket_path, file_prefix);
7236}
7237
7238int RGWBulkUploadOp::handle_dir_verify_permission(optional_yield y)
7239{
7240 if (s->user->get_max_buckets() > 0) {
7241 rgw::sal::BucketList buckets;
7242 std::string marker;
7243 op_ret = s->user->list_buckets(this, marker, std::string(), s->user->get_max_buckets(),
7244 false, buckets, y);
7245 if (op_ret < 0) {
7246 return op_ret;
7247 }
7248
7249 if (buckets.count() >= static_cast<size_t>(s->user->get_max_buckets())) {
7250 return -ERR_TOO_MANY_BUCKETS;
7251 }
7252 }
7253
7254 return 0;
7255}
7256
7257static void forward_req_info(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, CephContext *cct, req_info& info, const std::string& bucket_name)
7258{
7259 /* the request of container or object level will contain bucket name.
7260 * only at account level need to append the bucket name */
7261 if (info.script_uri.find(bucket_name) != std::string::npos) {
7262 return;
7263 }
7264
7265 ldpp_dout(dpp, 20) << "append the bucket: "<< bucket_name << " to req_info" << dendl;
7266 info.script_uri.append("/").append(bucket_name);
7267 info.request_uri_aws4 = info.request_uri = info.script_uri;
7268 info.effective_uri = "/" + bucket_name;
7269}
7270
7271void RGWBulkUploadOp::init(rgw::sal::Store* const store,
7272 struct req_state* const s,
7273 RGWHandler* const h)
7274{
7275 RGWOp::init(store, s, h);
7276}
7277
7278int RGWBulkUploadOp::handle_dir(const std::string_view path, optional_yield y)
7279{
7280 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "got directory=" << path << dendl;
7281
7282 op_ret = handle_dir_verify_permission(y);
7283 if (op_ret < 0) {
7284 return op_ret;
7285 }
7286
7287 std::string bucket_name;
7288 rgw_obj_key object_junk;
7289 std::tie(bucket_name, object_junk) = *parse_path(path);
7290
7291 rgw_raw_obj obj(store->get_zone()->get_params().domain_root,
7292 rgw_make_bucket_entry_name(s->bucket_tenant, bucket_name));
7293
7294 /* we need to make sure we read bucket info, it's not read before for this
7295 * specific request */
7296 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Bucket> bucket;
7297
7298 /* Create metadata: ACLs. */
7299 std::map<std::string, ceph::bufferlist> attrs;
7300 RGWAccessControlPolicy policy;
7301 policy.create_default(s->user->get_id(), s->user->get_display_name());
7302 ceph::bufferlist aclbl;
7303 policy.encode(aclbl);
7304 attrs.emplace(RGW_ATTR_ACL, std::move(aclbl));
7305
7306 obj_version objv, ep_objv;
7307 bool bucket_exists;
7308 RGWQuotaInfo quota_info;
7309 const RGWQuotaInfo* pquota_info = nullptr;
7310 RGWBucketInfo out_info;
7311 string swift_ver_location;
7312 rgw_bucket new_bucket;
7313 req_info info = s->info;
7314 new_bucket.tenant = s->bucket_tenant; /* ignored if bucket exists */
7315 new_bucket.name = bucket_name;
7316 rgw_placement_rule placement_rule;
7317 placement_rule.storage_class = s->info.storage_class;
7318 forward_req_info(this, s->cct, info, bucket_name);
7319
7320 op_ret = s->user->create_bucket(this, new_bucket,
7321 store->get_zone()->get_zonegroup().get_id(),
7322 placement_rule, swift_ver_location,
7323 pquota_info, policy, attrs,
7324 out_info, ep_objv,
7325 true, false, &bucket_exists,
7326 info, &bucket, y);
7327 /* continue if EEXIST and create_bucket will fail below. this way we can
7328 * recover from a partial create by retrying it. */
7329 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "rgw_create_bucket returned ret=" << op_ret
7330 << ", bucket=" << bucket << dendl;
7331
7332 return op_ret;
7333}
7334
7335
7336bool RGWBulkUploadOp::handle_file_verify_permission(RGWBucketInfo& binfo,
7337 const rgw_obj& obj,
7338 std::map<std::string, ceph::bufferlist>& battrs,
7339 ACLOwner& bucket_owner /* out */,
7340 optional_yield y)
7341{
7342 RGWAccessControlPolicy bacl(store->ctx());
7343 op_ret = read_bucket_policy(this, store, s, binfo, battrs, &bacl, binfo.bucket, y);
7344 if (op_ret < 0) {
7345 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "cannot read_policy() for bucket" << dendl;
7346 return false;
7347 }
7348
7349 auto policy = get_iam_policy_from_attr(s->cct, battrs, binfo.bucket.tenant);
7350
7351 bucket_owner = bacl.get_owner();
7352 if (policy || ! s->iam_user_policies.empty() || !s->session_policies.empty()) {
7353 auto identity_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->iam_user_policies, s->env,
7354 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject, obj);
7355 if (identity_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
7356 return false;
7357 }
7358
7359 rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal princ_type = rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other;
7360 ARN obj_arn(obj);
7361 auto e = policy->eval(s->env, *s->auth.identity,
7362 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject, obj_arn, princ_type);
7363 if (e == Effect::Deny) {
7364 return false;
7365 }
7366
7367 if (!s->session_policies.empty()) {
7368 auto session_policy_res = eval_identity_or_session_policies(s->session_policies, s->env,
7369 rgw::IAM::s3PutObject, obj);
7370 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Deny) {
7371 return false;
7372 }
7373 if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Role) {
7374 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus intersection of session policy and bucket policy
7375 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) ||
7376 (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && e == Effect::Allow)) {
7377 return true;
7378 }
7379 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Session) {
7380 //Intersection of session policy and identity policy plus bucket policy
7381 if ((session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) || e == Effect::Allow) {
7382 return true;
7383 }
7384 } else if (princ_type == rgw::IAM::PolicyPrincipal::Other) {// there was no match in the bucket policy
7385 if (session_policy_res == Effect::Allow && identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) {
7386 return true;
7387 }
7388 }
7389 return false;
7390 }
7391 if (e == Effect::Allow || identity_policy_res == Effect::Allow) {
7392 return true;
7393 }
7394 }
7395
7396 return verify_bucket_permission_no_policy(this, s, s->user_acl.get(),
7397 &bacl, RGW_PERM_WRITE);
7398}
7399
7400int RGWBulkUploadOp::handle_file(const std::string_view path,
7401 const size_t size,
7402 AlignedStreamGetter& body, optional_yield y)
7403{
7404
7405 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "got file=" << path << ", size=" << size << dendl;
7406
7407 if (size > static_cast<size_t>(s->cct->_conf->rgw_max_put_size)) {
7408 op_ret = -ERR_TOO_LARGE;
7409 return op_ret;
7410 }
7411
7412 std::string bucket_name;
7413 rgw_obj_key object;
7414 std::tie(bucket_name, object) = *parse_path(path);
7415
7416 auto& obj_ctx = *static_cast<RGWObjectCtx *>(s->obj_ctx);
7417 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Bucket> bucket;
7418 ACLOwner bowner;
7419
7420 op_ret = store->get_bucket(this, s->user.get(), rgw_bucket(rgw_bucket_key(s->user->get_tenant(), bucket_name)), &bucket, y);
7421 if (op_ret < 0) {
7422 if (op_ret == -ENOENT) {
7423 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "non existent directory=" << bucket_name << dendl;
7424 }
7425 return op_ret;
7426 }
7427
7428 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Object> obj = bucket->get_object(object);
7429
7430 if (! handle_file_verify_permission(bucket->get_info(),
7431 obj->get_obj(),
7432 bucket->get_attrs(), bowner, y)) {
7433 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "object creation unauthorized" << dendl;
7434 op_ret = -EACCES;
7435 return op_ret;
7436 }
7437
7438 op_ret = bucket->check_quota(this, user_quota, bucket_quota, size, y);
7439 if (op_ret < 0) {
7440 return op_ret;
7441 }
7442
7443 if (bucket->versioning_enabled()) {
7444 obj->gen_rand_obj_instance_name();
7445 }
7446
7447 rgw_placement_rule dest_placement = s->dest_placement;
7448 dest_placement.inherit_from(bucket->get_placement_rule());
7449
7450 std::unique_ptr<rgw::sal::Writer> processor;
7451 processor = store->get_atomic_writer(this, s->yield, std::move(obj),
7452 bowner.get_id(), obj_ctx,
7453 &s->dest_placement, 0, s->req_id);
7454 op_ret = processor->prepare(s->yield);
7455 if (op_ret < 0) {
7456 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "cannot prepare processor due to ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
7457 return op_ret;
7458 }
7459
7460 /* No filters by default. */
7461 rgw::sal::DataProcessor *filter = processor.get();
7462
7463 const auto& compression_type = store->get_zone()->get_params().get_compression_type(
7464 dest_placement);
7465 CompressorRef plugin;
7466 boost::optional<RGWPutObj_Compress> compressor;
7467 if (compression_type != "none") {
7468 plugin = Compressor::create(s->cct, compression_type);
7469 if (! plugin) {
7470 ldpp_dout(this, 1) << "Cannot load plugin for rgw_compression_type "
7471 << compression_type << dendl;
7472 } else {
7473 compressor.emplace(s->cct, plugin, filter);
7474 filter = &*compressor;
7475 }
7476 }
7477
7478 /* Upload file content. */
7479 ssize_t len = 0;
7480 size_t ofs = 0;
7481 MD5 hash;
7482 // Allow use of MD5 digest in FIPS mode for non-cryptographic purposes
7483 hash.SetFlags(EVP_MD_CTX_FLAG_NON_FIPS_ALLOW);
7484 do {
7485 ceph::bufferlist data;
7486 len = body.get_at_most(s->cct->_conf->rgw_max_chunk_size, data);
7487
7488 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "body=" << data.c_str() << dendl;
7489 if (len < 0) {
7490 op_ret = len;
7491 return op_ret;
7492 } else if (len > 0) {
7493 hash.Update((const unsigned char *)data.c_str(), data.length());
7494 op_ret = filter->process(std::move(data), ofs);
7495 if (op_ret < 0) {
7496 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "filter->process() returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
7497 return op_ret;
7498 }
7499
7500 ofs += len;
7501 }
7502
7503 } while (len > 0);
7504
7505 // flush
7506 op_ret = filter->process({}, ofs);
7507 if (op_ret < 0) {
7508 return op_ret;
7509 }
7510
7511 if (ofs != size) {
7512 ldpp_dout(this, 10) << "real file size different from declared" << dendl;
7513 op_ret = -EINVAL;
7514 return op_ret;
7515 }
7516
7517 op_ret = bucket->check_quota(this, user_quota, bucket_quota, size, y);
7518 if (op_ret < 0) {
7519 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "quota exceeded for path=" << path << dendl;
7520 return op_ret;
7521 }
7522
7523 char calc_md5[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE * 2 + 1];
7524 unsigned char m[CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE];
7525 hash.Final(m);
7526 buf_to_hex(m, CEPH_CRYPTO_MD5_DIGESTSIZE, calc_md5);
7527
7528 /* Create metadata: ETAG. */
7529 std::map<std::string, ceph::bufferlist> attrs;
7530 std::string etag = calc_md5;
7531 ceph::bufferlist etag_bl;
7532 etag_bl.append(etag.c_str(), etag.size() + 1);
7533 attrs.emplace(RGW_ATTR_ETAG, std::move(etag_bl));
7534
7535 /* Create metadata: ACLs. */
7536 RGWAccessControlPolicy policy;
7537 policy.create_default(s->user->get_id(), s->user->get_display_name());
7538 ceph::bufferlist aclbl;
7539 policy.encode(aclbl);
7540 attrs.emplace(RGW_ATTR_ACL, std::move(aclbl));
7541
7542 /* Create metadata: compression info. */
7543 if (compressor && compressor->is_compressed()) {
7544 ceph::bufferlist tmp;
7545 RGWCompressionInfo cs_info;
7546 cs_info.compression_type = plugin->get_type_name();
7547 cs_info.orig_size = size;
7548 cs_info.compressor_message = compressor->get_compressor_message();
7549 cs_info.blocks = std::move(compressor->get_compression_blocks());
7550 encode(cs_info, tmp);
7551 attrs.emplace(RGW_ATTR_COMPRESSION, std::move(tmp));
7552 }
7553
7554 /* Complete the transaction. */
7555 op_ret = processor->complete(size, etag, nullptr, ceph::real_time(),
7556 attrs, ceph::real_time() /* delete_at */,
7557 nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr,
7558 s->yield);
7559 if (op_ret < 0) {
7560 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "processor::complete returned op_ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
7561 }
7562
7563 return op_ret;
7564}
7565
7566void RGWBulkUploadOp::execute(optional_yield y)
7567{
7568 ceph::bufferlist buffer(64 * 1024);
7569
7570 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "start" << dendl;
7571
7572 /* Create an instance of stream-abstracting class. Having this indirection
7573 * allows for easy introduction of decompressors like gzip and bzip2. */
7574 auto stream = create_stream();
7575 if (! stream) {
7576 return;
7577 }
7578
7579 /* Handling the $UPLOAD_PATH accordingly to the Swift's Bulk middleware. See:
7580 * https://github.com/openstack/swift/blob/2.13.0/swift/common/middleware/bulk.py#L31-L41 */
7581 std::string bucket_path, file_prefix;
7582 std::tie(bucket_path, file_prefix) = handle_upload_path(s);
7583
7584 auto status = rgw::tar::StatusIndicator::create();
7585 do {
7586 op_ret = stream->get_exactly(rgw::tar::BLOCK_SIZE, buffer);
7587 if (op_ret < 0) {
7588 ldpp_dout(this, 2) << "cannot read header" << dendl;
7589 return;
7590 }
7591
7592 /* We need to re-interpret the buffer as a TAR block. Exactly two blocks
7593 * must be tracked to detect out end-of-archive. It occurs when both of
7594 * them are empty (zeroed). Tracing this particular inter-block dependency
7595 * is responsibility of the rgw::tar::StatusIndicator class. */
7596 boost::optional<rgw::tar::HeaderView> header;
7597 std::tie(status, header) = rgw::tar::interpret_block(status, buffer);
7598
7599 if (! status.empty() && header) {
7600 /* This specific block isn't empty (entirely zeroed), so we can parse
7601 * it as a TAR header and dispatch. At the moment we do support only
7602 * regular files and directories. Everything else (symlinks, devices)
7603 * will be ignored but won't cease the whole upload. */
7604 switch (header->get_filetype()) {
7605 case rgw::tar::FileType::NORMAL_FILE: {
7606 ldpp_dout(this, 2) << "handling regular file" << dendl;
7607
7608 std::string_view filename;
7609 if (bucket_path.empty())
7610 filename = header->get_filename();
7611 else
7612 filename = file_prefix + std::string(header->get_filename());
7613 auto body = AlignedStreamGetter(0, header->get_filesize(),
7614 rgw::tar::BLOCK_SIZE, *stream);
7615 op_ret = handle_file(filename,
7616 header->get_filesize(),
7617 body, y);
7618 if (! op_ret) {
7619 /* Only regular files counts. */
7620 num_created++;
7621 } else {
7622 failures.emplace_back(op_ret, std::string(filename));
7623 }
7624 break;
7625 }
7626 case rgw::tar::FileType::DIRECTORY: {
7627 ldpp_dout(this, 2) << "handling regular directory" << dendl;
7628
7629 std::string_view dirname = bucket_path.empty() ? header->get_filename() : bucket_path;
7630 op_ret = handle_dir(dirname, y);
7631 if (op_ret < 0 && op_ret != -ERR_BUCKET_EXISTS) {
7632 failures.emplace_back(op_ret, std::string(dirname));
7633 }
7634 break;
7635 }
7636 default: {
7637 /* Not recognized. Skip. */
7638 op_ret = 0;
7639 break;
7640 }
7641 }
7642
7643 /* In case of any problems with sub-request authorization Swift simply
7644 * terminates whole upload immediately. */
7645 if (boost::algorithm::contains(std::initializer_list<int>{ op_ret },
7646 terminal_errors)) {
7647 ldpp_dout(this, 2) << "terminating due to ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
7648 break;
7649 }
7650 } else {
7651 ldpp_dout(this, 2) << "an empty block" << dendl;
7652 op_ret = 0;
7653 }
7654
7655 buffer.clear();
7656 } while (! status.eof());
7657
7658 return;
7659}
7660
7661RGWBulkUploadOp::AlignedStreamGetter::~AlignedStreamGetter()
7662{
7663 const size_t aligned_legnth = length + (-length % alignment);
7664 ceph::bufferlist junk;
7665
7666 DecoratedStreamGetter::get_exactly(aligned_legnth - position, junk);
7667}
7668
7669ssize_t RGWBulkUploadOp::AlignedStreamGetter::get_at_most(const size_t want,
7670 ceph::bufferlist& dst)
7671{
7672 const size_t max_to_read = std::min(want, length - position);
7673 const auto len = DecoratedStreamGetter::get_at_most(max_to_read, dst);
7674 if (len > 0) {
7675 position += len;
7676 }
7677 return len;
7678}
7679
7680ssize_t RGWBulkUploadOp::AlignedStreamGetter::get_exactly(const size_t want,
7681 ceph::bufferlist& dst)
7682{
7683 const auto len = DecoratedStreamGetter::get_exactly(want, dst);
7684 if (len > 0) {
7685 position += len;
7686 }
7687 return len;
7688}
7689
7690int RGWGetAttrs::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
7691{
7692 s->object->set_atomic(s->obj_ctx);
7693
7694 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s);
7695 if (has_s3_existing_tag || has_s3_resource_tag)
7696 rgw_iam_add_objtags(this, s, has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag);
7697
7698 auto iam_action = s->object->get_instance().empty() ?
7699 rgw::IAM::s3GetObject :
7700 rgw::IAM::s3GetObjectVersion;
7701
7702 if (!verify_object_permission(this, s, iam_action)) {
7703 return -EACCES;
7704 }
7705
7706 return 0;
7707}
7708
7709void RGWGetAttrs::pre_exec()
7710{
7711 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
7712}
7713
7714void RGWGetAttrs::execute(optional_yield y)
7715{
7716 op_ret = get_params();
7717 if (op_ret < 0)
7718 return;
7719
7720 s->object->set_atomic(s->obj_ctx);
7721
7722 op_ret = s->object->get_obj_attrs(s->obj_ctx, s->yield, this);
7723 if (op_ret < 0) {
7724 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: failed to get obj attrs, obj=" << s->object
7725 << " ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
7726 return;
7727 }
7728
7729 /* XXX RGWObject::get_obj_attrs() does not support filtering (yet) */
7730 auto& obj_attrs = s->object->get_attrs();
7731 if (attrs.size() != 0) {
7732 /* return only attrs requested */
7733 for (auto& att : attrs) {
7734 auto iter = obj_attrs.find(att.first);
7735 if (iter != obj_attrs.end()) {
7736 att.second = iter->second;
7737 }
7738 }
7739 } else {
7740 /* return all attrs */
7741 for (auto& att : obj_attrs) {
7742 attrs.insert(get_attrs_t::value_type(att.first, att.second));;
7743 }
7744 }
7745
7746 return;
7747 }
7748
7749int RGWRMAttrs::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
7750{
7751 // This looks to be part of the RGW-NFS machinery and has no S3 or
7752 // Swift equivalent.
7753 bool perm;
7754 if (!rgw::sal::Object::empty(s->object.get())) {
7755 perm = verify_object_permission_no_policy(this, s, RGW_PERM_WRITE);
7756 } else {
7757 perm = verify_bucket_permission_no_policy(this, s, RGW_PERM_WRITE);
7758 }
7759 if (!perm)
7760 return -EACCES;
7761
7762 return 0;
7763}

7766{

7768}

7770void RGWRMAttrs::execute(optional_yield y)
7771{
7772 op_ret = get_params();
7773 if (op_ret < 0)
7774 return;
7775
7776 s->object->set_atomic(s->obj_ctx);
7777
7778 op_ret = s->object->set_obj_attrs(this, s->obj_ctx, nullptr, &attrs, y);
7779 if (op_ret < 0) {
7780 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: failed to delete obj attrs, obj=" << s->object
7781 << " ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
7782 }
7783 return;
7784}

7920
7921int RGWHandler::do_init_permissions(const DoutPrefixProvider *dpp, optional_yield y)
7922{
7923 int ret = rgw_build_bucket_policies(dpp, store, s, y);
7924 if (ret < 0) {
7925 ldpp_dout(dpp, 10) << "init_permissions on " << s->bucket
7926 << " failed, ret=" << ret << dendl;
7927 return ret==-ENODATA ? -EACCES : ret;
7928 }
7929
7930 rgw_build_iam_environment(store, s);
7931 return ret;
7932}
7933
7934int RGWHandler::do_read_permissions(RGWOp *op, bool only_bucket, optional_yield y)
7935{
7936 if (only_bucket) {
7937 /* already read bucket info */
7938 return 0;
7939 }
7940 int ret = rgw_build_object_policies(op, store, s, op->prefetch_data(), y);
7941
7942 if (ret < 0) {
7943 ldpp_dout(op, 10) << "read_permissions on " << s->bucket << ":"
7944 << s->object << " only_bucket=" << only_bucket
7945 << " ret=" << ret << dendl;
7946 if (ret == -ENODATA)
7947 ret = -EACCES;
7948 if (s->auth.identity->is_anonymous() && ret == -EACCES)
7949 ret = -EPERM;
7950 }
7951
7952 return ret;
7953}

7969
7970void RGWDefaultResponseOp::send_response() {
7971 if (op_ret) {
7972 set_req_state_err(s, op_ret);
7973 }
7974 dump_errno(s);
7975 end_header(s);
7976}
7977
7978void RGWPutBucketPolicy::send_response()
7979{
7980 if (!op_ret) {
7981 /* A successful Put Bucket Policy should return a 204 on success */
7982 op_ret = STATUS_NO_CONTENT;
7983 }
7984 if (op_ret) {
7985 set_req_state_err(s, op_ret);
7986 }
7987 dump_errno(s);
7988 end_header(s);
7989}
7990
7991int RGWPutBucketPolicy::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
7992{
7993 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s, false);
7994 if (has_s3_resource_tag)
7995 rgw_iam_add_buckettags(this, s);
7996
7997 if (!verify_bucket_permission(this, s, rgw::IAM::s3PutBucketPolicy)) {
7998 return -EACCES;
7999 }
8000
8001 return 0;
8002}
8003
8004int RGWPutBucketPolicy::get_params(optional_yield y)
8005{
8006 const auto max_size = s->cct->_conf->rgw_max_put_param_size;
8007 // At some point when I have more time I want to make a version of
8008 // rgw_rest_read_all_input that doesn't use malloc.
8009 std::tie(op_ret, data) = read_all_input(s, max_size, false);
8010
8011 // And throws exceptions.
8012 return op_ret;
8013}
8014
8015void RGWPutBucketPolicy::execute(optional_yield y)
8016{
8017 op_ret = get_params(y);
8018 if (op_ret < 0) {
8019 return;
8020 }
8021
8022 op_ret = store->forward_request_to_master(this, s->user.get(), nullptr, data, nullptr, s->info, y);
8023 if (op_ret < 0) {
8024 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "forward_request_to_master returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
8025 return;
8026 }
8027
8028 try {
8029 const Policy p(s->cct, s->bucket_tenant, data);
8030 rgw::sal::Attrs attrs(s->bucket_attrs);
8031 if (s->bucket_access_conf &&
8032 s->bucket_access_conf->block_public_policy() &&
8033 rgw::IAM::is_public(p)) {
8034 op_ret = -EACCES;
8035 return;
8036 }
8037
8038 op_ret = retry_raced_bucket_write(this, s->bucket.get(), [&p, this, &attrs] {
8039 attrs[RGW_ATTR_IAM_POLICY].clear();
8040 attrs[RGW_ATTR_IAM_POLICY].append(p.text);
8041 op_ret = s->bucket->merge_and_store_attrs(this, attrs, s->yield);
8042 return op_ret;
8043 });
8044 } catch (rgw::IAM::PolicyParseException& e) {
8045 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "failed to parse policy: " << e.what() << dendl;
8046 op_ret = -EINVAL;
8047 }
8048}
8049
8050void RGWGetBucketPolicy::send_response()
8051{
8052 if (op_ret) {
8053 set_req_state_err(s, op_ret);
8054 }
8055 dump_errno(s);
8056 end_header(s, this, "application/json");
8057 dump_body(s, policy);
8058}
8059
8060int RGWGetBucketPolicy::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
8061{
8062 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s, false);
8063 if (has_s3_resource_tag)
8064 rgw_iam_add_buckettags(this, s);
8065
8066 if (!verify_bucket_permission(this, s, rgw::IAM::s3GetBucketPolicy)) {
8067 return -EACCES;
8068 }
8069
8070 return 0;
8071}
8072
8073void RGWGetBucketPolicy::execute(optional_yield y)
8074{
8075 rgw::sal::Attrs attrs(s->bucket_attrs);
8076 auto aiter = attrs.find(RGW_ATTR_IAM_POLICY);
8077 if (aiter == attrs.end()) {
8078 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "can't find bucket IAM POLICY attr bucket_name = "
8079 << s->bucket_name << dendl;
8080 op_ret = -ERR_NO_SUCH_BUCKET_POLICY;
8081 s->err.message = "The bucket policy does not exist";
8082 return;
8083 } else {
8084 policy = attrs[RGW_ATTR_IAM_POLICY];
8085
8086 if (policy.length() == 0) {
8087 ldpp_dout(this, 10) << "The bucket policy does not exist, bucket: "
8088 << s->bucket_name << dendl;
8089 op_ret = -ERR_NO_SUCH_BUCKET_POLICY;
8090 s->err.message = "The bucket policy does not exist";
8091 return;
8092 }
8093 }
8094}

8124 return;

8141{
8142 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s, false);
8143 if (has_s3_resource_tag)

8148
8149void RGWPutBucketObjectLock::execute(optional_yield y)
8150{
8151 if (!s->bucket->get_info().obj_lock_enabled()) {
8152 s->err.message = "object lock configuration can't be set if bucket object lock not enabled";
8153 ldpp_dout(this, 4) << "ERROR: " << s->err.message << dendl;
8154 op_ret = -ERR_INVALID_BUCKET_STATE;
8155 return;
8156 }
8157
8158 RGWXMLDecoder::XMLParser parser;
8159 if (!parser.init()) {
8160 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: failed to initialize parser" << dendl;
8161 op_ret = -EINVAL;
8162 return;
8163 }
8164 op_ret = get_params(y);
8165 if (op_ret < 0) {
8166 return;
8167 }
8168 if (!parser.parse(data.c_str(), data.length(), 1)) {
8169 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;
8170 return;
8171 }
8172
8173 try {
8174 RGWXMLDecoder::decode_xml("ObjectLockConfiguration", obj_lock, &parser, true);
8175 } catch (RGWXMLDecoder::err& err) {
8176 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << "unexpected xml:" << err << dendl;
8177 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;
8178 return;
8179 }
8180 if (obj_lock.has_rule() && !obj_lock.retention_period_valid()) {
8181 s->err.message = "retention period must be a positive integer value";
8182 ldpp_dout(this, 4) << "ERROR: " << s->err.message << dendl;
8183 op_ret = -ERR_INVALID_RETENTION_PERIOD;
8184 return;
8185 }
8186
8187 op_ret = store->forward_request_to_master(this, s->user.get(), nullptr, data, nullptr, s->info, y);
8188 if (op_ret < 0) {
8189 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << __func__ << "forward_request_to_master returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
8190 return;
8191 }
8192
8193 op_ret = retry_raced_bucket_write(this, s->bucket.get(), [this] {
8194 s->bucket->get_info().obj_lock = obj_lock;
8195 op_ret = s->bucket->put_info(this, false, real_time());
8196 return op_ret;
8197 });
8198 return;
8199}

8204}

8209 if (has_s3_resource_tag)

8211
8212 return verify_bucket_owner_or_policy(s, rgw::IAM::s3GetBucketObjectLockConfiguration);
8213}

8218 op_ret = -ERR_NO_SUCH_OBJECT_LOCK_CONFIGURATION;
8219 return;
8220 }
8221}
8222
8223int RGWPutObjRetention::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
8224{
8225 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s);
8226 if (has_s3_existing_tag || has_s3_resource_tag)
8227 rgw_iam_add_objtags(this, s, has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag);
8228
8229 if (!verify_object_permission(this, s, rgw::IAM::s3PutObjectRetention)) {
8230 return -EACCES;
8231 }
8232 op_ret = get_params(y);
8233 if (op_ret) {
8234 return op_ret;
8235 }
8236 if (bypass_governance_mode) {
8237 bypass_perm = verify_object_permission(this, s, rgw::IAM::s3BypassGovernanceRetention);
8238 }
8239 return 0;
8240}
8241
8242void RGWPutObjRetention::pre_exec()
8243{
8244 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);
8245}
8246
8247void RGWPutObjRetention::execute(optional_yield y)
8248{
8249 if (!s->bucket->get_info().obj_lock_enabled()) {
8250 s->err.message = "object retention can't be set if bucket object lock not configured";
8251 ldpp_dout(this, 4) << "ERROR: " << s->err.message << dendl;
8252 op_ret = -ERR_INVALID_REQUEST;
8253 return;
8254 }
8255
8256 RGWXMLDecoder::XMLParser parser;
8257 if (!parser.init()) {
8258 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: failed to initialize parser" << dendl;
8259 op_ret = -EINVAL;
8260 return;
8261 }
8262
8263 if (!parser.parse(data.c_str(), data.length(), 1)) {
8264 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;
8265 return;
8266 }
8267
8268 try {
8269 RGWXMLDecoder::decode_xml("Retention", obj_retention, &parser, true);
8270 } catch (RGWXMLDecoder::err& err) {
8271 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << "unexpected xml:" << err << dendl;
8272 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;
8273 return;
8274 }
8275
8276 if (ceph::real_clock::to_time_t(obj_retention.get_retain_until_date()) < ceph_clock_now()) {
8277 s->err.message = "the retain-until date must be in the future";
8278 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: " << s->err.message << dendl;
8279 op_ret = -EINVAL;
8280 return;
8281 }
8282 bufferlist bl;
8283 obj_retention.encode(bl);
8284
8285 //check old retention
8286 op_ret = s->object->get_obj_attrs(s->obj_ctx, s->yield, this);
8287 if (op_ret < 0) {
8288 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: get obj attr error"<< dendl;
8289 return;
8290 }
8291 rgw::sal::Attrs attrs = s->object->get_attrs();
8292 auto aiter = attrs.find(RGW_ATTR_OBJECT_RETENTION);
8293 if (aiter != attrs.end()) {
8294 RGWObjectRetention old_obj_retention;
8295 try {
8296 decode(old_obj_retention, aiter->second);
8297 } catch (buffer::error& err) {
8298 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: failed to decode RGWObjectRetention" << dendl;
8299 op_ret = -EIO;
8300 return;
8301 }
8302 if (ceph::real_clock::to_time_t(obj_retention.get_retain_until_date()) < ceph::real_clock::to_time_t(old_obj_retention.get_retain_until_date())) {
8303 if (old_obj_retention.get_mode().compare("GOVERNANCE") != 0 || !bypass_perm || !bypass_governance_mode) {
8304 s->err.message = "proposed retain-until date shortens an existing retention period and governance bypass check failed";
8305 op_ret = -EACCES;
8306 return;
8307 }
8308 } else if (old_obj_retention.get_mode() == obj_retention.get_mode()) {
8309 // ok if retention mode doesn't change
8310 } else if (obj_retention.get_mode() == "GOVERNANCE") {
8311 s->err.message = "can't change retention mode from COMPLIANCE to GOVERNANCE";
8312 op_ret = -EACCES;
8313 return;
8314 } else if (!bypass_perm || !bypass_governance_mode) {
8315 s->err.message = "can't change retention mode from GOVERNANCE without governance bypass";
8316 op_ret = -EACCES;
8317 return;
8318 }
8319 }
8320
8321 op_ret = s->object->modify_obj_attrs(s->obj_ctx, RGW_ATTR_OBJECT_RETENTION, bl, s->yield, this);
8322
8323 return;
8324}
8325
8326int RGWGetObjRetention::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
8327{
8328 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s);
8329 if (has_s3_existing_tag || has_s3_resource_tag)
8330 rgw_iam_add_objtags(this, s, has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag);
8331
8332 if (!verify_object_permission(this, s, rgw::IAM::s3GetObjectRetention)) {
8333 return -EACCES;
8334 }
8335 return 0;
8336}

8340 rgw_bucket_object_pre_exec(s);

8343void RGWGetObjRetention::execute(optional_yield y)
8344{
8345 if (!s->bucket->get_info().obj_lock_enabled()) {
8346 s->err.message = "bucket object lock not configured";
8347 ldpp_dout(this, 4) << "ERROR: " << s->err.message << dendl;
8348 op_ret = -ERR_INVALID_REQUEST;
8349 return;
8350 }
8351 op_ret = s->object->get_obj_attrs(s->obj_ctx, s->yield, this);
8352 if (op_ret < 0) {
8353 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: failed to get obj attrs, obj=" << s->object
8354 << " ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
8355 return;
8356 }
8357 rgw::sal::Attrs attrs = s->object->get_attrs();
8358 auto aiter = attrs.find(RGW_ATTR_OBJECT_RETENTION);
8359 if (aiter == attrs.end()) {
8360 op_ret = -ERR_NO_SUCH_OBJECT_LOCK_CONFIGURATION;
8361 return;
8362 }
8363
8364 bufferlist::const_iterator iter{&aiter->second};
8365 try {
8366 obj_retention.decode(iter);
8367 } catch (const buffer::error& e) {
8368 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << __func__ << "decode object retention config failed" << dendl;
8369 op_ret = -EIO;
8370 return;
8371 }
8372 return;
8373}

8522void RGWPutBucketPublicAccessBlock::execute(optional_yield y)
8523{

8526 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: failed to initialize parser" << dendl;
8527 op_ret = -EINVAL;
8528 return;
8529 }
8530
8531 op_ret = get_params(y);
8532 if (op_ret < 0)
8533 return;
8534
8535 if (!parser.parse(data.c_str(), data.length(), 1)) {
8536 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: malformed XML" << dendl;
8537 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;
8538 return;

8540

8542 RGWXMLDecoder::decode_xml("PublicAccessBlockConfiguration", access_conf, &parser, true);

8545 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;

8550 if (op_ret < 0) {
8551 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "forward_request_to_master returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
8552 return;
8553 }
8554
8555 bufferlist bl;
8556 access_conf.encode(bl);
8557 op_ret = retry_raced_bucket_write(this, s->bucket.get(), [this, &bl] {
8558 rgw::sal::Attrs attrs(s->bucket_attrs);

8565int RGWGetBucketPublicAccessBlock::verify_permission(optional_yield y)

8568 if (has_s3_resource_tag)
8569 rgw_iam_add_buckettags(this, s);

8574

8577
8578void RGWGetBucketPublicAccessBlock::execute(optional_yield y)
8579{
8580 auto attrs = s->bucket_attrs;
8581 if (auto aiter = attrs.find(RGW_ATTR_PUBLIC_ACCESS);
8582 aiter == attrs.end()) {
8583 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "can't find bucket IAM POLICY attr bucket_name = "
8584 << s->bucket_name << dendl;
8585 // return the default;
8586 return;
8587 } else {
8588 bufferlist::const_iterator iter{&aiter->second};
8589 try {
8590 access_conf.decode(iter);
8591 } catch (const buffer::error& e) {
8592 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << __func__ << "decode access_conf failed" << dendl;
8593 op_ret = -EIO;
8594 return;
8595 }
8596 }
8597}
8598
8599
8600void RGWDeleteBucketPublicAccessBlock::send_response()
8601{
8602 if (op_ret) {
8603 set_req_state_err(s, op_ret);
8604 }
8605 dump_errno(s);
8606 end_header(s);
8607}
8608
8609int RGWDeleteBucketPublicAccessBlock::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
8610{
8611 auto [has_s3_existing_tag, has_s3_resource_tag] = rgw_check_policy_condition(this, s, false);
8612 if (has_s3_resource_tag)
8613 rgw_iam_add_buckettags(this, s);
8614
8615 if (!verify_bucket_permission(this, s, rgw::IAM::s3PutBucketPublicAccessBlock)) {
8616 return -EACCES;
8617 }
8618
8619 return 0;
8620}
8621
8622void RGWDeleteBucketPublicAccessBlock::execute(optional_yield y)
8623{
8624 bufferlist data;
8625 op_ret = store->forward_request_to_master(this, s->user.get(), nullptr, data, nullptr, s->info, y);
8626 if (op_ret < 0) {
8627 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "forward_request_to_master returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
8628 return;
8629 }
8630
8631 op_ret = retry_raced_bucket_write(this, s->bucket.get(), [this] {
8632 rgw::sal::Attrs attrs(s->bucket_attrs);
8633 attrs.erase(RGW_ATTR_PUBLIC_ACCESS);
8634 op_ret = s->bucket->merge_and_store_attrs(this, attrs, s->yield);
8635 return op_ret;
8636 });
8637}

8640{
8641 const auto max_size = s->cct->_conf->rgw_max_put_param_size;
8642 std::tie(op_ret, data) = read_all_input(s, max_size, false);
8643 return op_ret;
8644}

8653
8654void RGWPutBucketEncryption::execute(optional_yield y)
8655{
8656 RGWXMLDecoder::XMLParser parser;
8657 if (!parser.init()) {
8658 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: failed to initialize parser" << dendl;
8659 op_ret = -EINVAL;
8660 return;
8661 }
8662 op_ret = get_params(y);
8663 if (op_ret < 0) {
8664 return;
8665 }
8666 if (!parser.parse(data.c_str(), data.length(), 1)) {
8667 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "ERROR: malformed XML" << dendl;
8668 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;
8669 return;
8670 }
8671
8672 try {
8673 RGWXMLDecoder::decode_xml("ServerSideEncryptionConfiguration", bucket_encryption_conf, &parser, true);
8674 } catch (RGWXMLDecoder::err& err) {
8675 ldpp_dout(this, 5) << "unexpected xml:" << err << dendl;
8676 op_ret = -ERR_MALFORMED_XML;
8677 return;
8678 }
8679
8680 op_ret = store->forward_request_to_master(this, s->user.get(), nullptr, data, nullptr, s->info, y);
8681 if (op_ret < 0) {
8682 ldpp_dout(this, 20) << "forward_request_to_master returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
8683 return;
8684 }
8685
8686 bufferlist conf_bl;
8687 bucket_encryption_conf.encode(conf_bl);
8688 op_ret = retry_raced_bucket_write(this, s->bucket.get(), [this, y, &conf_bl] {
8689 rgw::sal::Attrs attrs = s->bucket->get_attrs();
8690 attrs[RGW_ATTR_BUCKET_ENCRYPTION_POLICY] = conf_bl;
8691 return s->bucket->merge_and_store_attrs(this, attrs, y);
8692 });
8693}
8694
8695int RGWGetBucketEncryption::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
8696{
8697 if (!verify_bucket_permission(this, s, rgw::IAM::s3GetBucketEncryption)) {
8698 return -EACCES;
8699 }
8700 return 0;
8701}
8702
8703void RGWGetBucketEncryption::execute(optional_yield y)
8704{
8705 const auto& attrs = s->bucket_attrs;
8706 if (auto aiter = attrs.find(RGW_ATTR_BUCKET_ENCRYPTION_POLICY);
8707 aiter == attrs.end()) {
8708 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "can't find BUCKET ENCRYPTION attr for bucket_name = " << s->bucket_name << dendl;
8709 op_ret = -ENOENT;
8710 s->err.message = "The server side encryption configuration was not found";
8711 return;
8712 } else {
8713 bufferlist::const_iterator iter{&aiter->second};
8714 try {
8715 bucket_encryption_conf.decode(iter);
8716 } catch (const buffer::error& e) {
8717 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << __func__ << "decode bucket_encryption_conf failed" << dendl;
8718 op_ret = -EIO;
8719 return;
8720 }
8721 }
8722}
8723
8724int RGWDeleteBucketEncryption::verify_permission(optional_yield y)
8725{
8726 if (!verify_bucket_permission(this, s, rgw::IAM::s3PutBucketEncryption)) {
8727 return -EACCES;
8728 }
8729 return 0;
8730}
8731
8732void RGWDeleteBucketEncryption::execute(optional_yield y)
8733{
8734 bufferlist data;
8735 op_ret = store->forward_request_to_master(this, s->user.get(), nullptr, data, nullptr, s->info, y);
8736 if (op_ret < 0) {
8737 ldpp_dout(this, 0) << "forward_request_to_master returned ret=" << op_ret << dendl;
8738 return;
8739 }
8740
8741 op_ret = retry_raced_bucket_write(this, s->bucket.get(), [this, y] {
8742 rgw::sal::Attrs attrs = s->bucket->get_attrs();
8743 attrs.erase(RGW_ATTR_BUCKET_ENCRYPTION_POLICY);
8744 attrs.erase(RGW_ATTR_BUCKET_ENCRYPTION_KEY_ID);
8745 op_ret = s->bucket->merge_and_store_attrs(this, attrs, y);
8746 return op_ret;
8747 });
8748}
